element.name: gpcAttributeValueName
element.definition: The GS1 provided text equivalent of the Global Product Classification Attribute Value Code.

element.name: flammableAerosolContainmentCode
element.definition: Determines whether the propellant in the trade item is an aerosol and whether the aerosol is considered flammable.

element.name: tradeItemKeyWords
element.definition: Words or phrases that enables web search engines to find trade items on the internet for example Shampoo, Lather, Baby.

element.name: childNutritionExpirationDateTime
element.definition: The date upon which the child nutrition statement or label expires.

element.name: fieldOfView
element.definition: Real field of view (field of vision) is the angle of the visible field, seen without moving the item, measured from the central point of the objective lens. In games the extent of the observable world that is seen at any given moment. This is used by such items as: microscope, rifle scope, cameras, binoculars are just some type of items. Measure in linear length or angular degrees for example 300 metres (MTR), 45 degrees(DD).

element.name: audioVisualMediaProductCollectionSeriesNumber
element.definition: Denotes which part of the series the media is part of for example Halloween II, Law & Order 7, South Park Season 12, Terminator 3, Star Wars II.

element.name: alternateText
element.definition: A detailed information pertaining to the image and the context for someone who is partially or fully visually impaired or blind

element.name: fileOptimalViewerName
element.definition: The software to which this file was targeted.

element.name: specialRequirementsDescription
element.definition: Any special requirements for storage or transportation in relation to any hazardous materials for example those regulated by ADR (European Agreement concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road).

element.name: audioVisualMediaProductCollectionName
element.definition: The name of a series of music publications grouped under a common theme. The name of the collection is printed on the package of the trade item.

element.name: lastChangeDate
element.definition: The date the party was last changed in the Global Registry

element.name: isPartyActive
element.definition: A Boolean field used to express whether the party is active or inactive used for tracking billing

element.name: freeQuantityOfProduct
element.definition: To indicate the quantity which is free. It is needed to update the price per unit of measure as displayed on the shelves. The unit of measure must be the same as the unit of measure of the Net Content. If the free quantity is expressed on the package it must be converted to a quantity expressed in the same unit of meas-ure as the net content in the message.

element.name: tradeItemTemperatureConditionTypeCode
element.definition: The condition of the product sold to the end consumer for example thawed or frozen.

element.name: globalModelRegulatoryAct
element.definition: The regulatory act that the Global Model Number is aligned to.

element.name: rugTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the usage or intended room for a particular type of rug.

element.name: sportCode
element.definition: A code indicating the sport associated with the product.

element.name: titlePrefixType
element.definition: Text at the beginning of a title element which is to be ignored for alphabetical sorting. Optional and non-repeating; can only be used if the <TitleWithoutPrefix> element is also present. These two elements may be used in combination in applications where it is necessary to distinguish an initial word or character string which is to be ignored for filing purposes, eg in library systems and in some bookshop databases.

element.name: materialAgencyCode
element.definition: This element indicates the agency that is maintaining the Trade Item Material codes. This may include a specific code list.

element.name: hazardousMaterialsHandlingProcedures
element.definition: Hazardous materials handling procedures are a description of how the product should be handled in relation to potential hazardous materials for example "do not handle around food, avoid contact with eyes, keep container closed.

element.name: minimumFishMeatPoultryContent
element.definition: The minimum amount of fish, meat or poultry contained in a food and beverage trade item expressed as a measurement.

element.name: cancelledDateTime
element.definition: Date on which the cancellation of the launch of a trade item what was never and will never be manufactured is made.

element.name: creditableAmount
element.definition: The creditable amount of the provided creditable ingredient as listed in the Creditable Ingredient Description and calculated as specified in the requirements, rules and regulations set forth by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body.

element.name: processCapabilityEffectiveEndDateTime
element.definition: The date at which the registration of a process capability is no longer effective.

element.name: consumerFirstDeliveryDate
element.definition: The first date/time that the buyer is allowed to deliver or ship the trade item to consumers. Usually related to a specific geography.

element.name: animalNutrientQuantityContainedBasis
element.definition: The basis amount that the animal nutrient quantity contained is measured against for example, 12 Kilograms in the case of 3 grams per 12 kilogram.

element.name: lethalConcentration50
element.definition: Median Lethal Concentration is a statistically derived concentration of a substance that can be expected to cause death in 50% of test animals. It is usually expressed as the weight of substance per weight or volume of water, air or feed, e.g., mg/l, mg/kg or ppm.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: Attribute value pair information.

element.name: specificGravityMeasurementPrecision
element.definition: The measurement precision used for the specific gravity for example EXACT.

element.name: organicClaimAgencyCode
element.definition: A Governing body that creates and maintains standards related to organic products.

element.name: microbiologicalOrganismWarningValue
element.definition: A microbiological limit which, in a 3–class plan, separates marginally acceptable quality from defective quality. Exceeding the limits of the allowed content of micro organisms defined as warning values indicating there is a poor quality of the hygiene standard in the food production. This would probably lead to health hazards.

element.name: foodBeverageCompositionCode
element.definition: A value assigned by the agency for the lookup of food composition information that applies to regulatory nutrition information e.g. R851011.

element.name: productActivityRegionDescription
element.definition: The region in which a processing or other activity has been performed for example bottling, farming, last processing.

element.name: additionalTradeItemClassificationCodeSequenceNumber
element.definition: A sequence number indicating the order number of the group of properties belonging together.

element.name: meatPoultryCut
element.definition: The description of a piece of meat that has been cut from an animal carcass. The determination of this is made by the supplier and is subject to target market regulations or trade organization guidelines.

element.name: restrictionDescription
element.definition: A description on any restrictions on usage for example locations where a pesticide cannot be sold.

element.name: hazardousSubstancesMinimizationCode
element.definition: Assessment and minimization of substances, or mixtures, hazardous to the environment in packaging constituents, components, or systems that are at risk of entering the environment.

element.name: dispenserTypeCode
element.definition: The mechanism or method by which the product is dispensed from its container.

element.name: workingPressureRatingMinimum
element.definition: The minimum approved working pressure rating for the product for a specific medium state (water, gas, etc).

element.name: distributionMethodCode
element.definition: The mode by which the Information Provider and the Party Receiving Private Data have agreed at what point(s) in the supply chain the Information Provider makes the goods available to the Party Receiving Private Data.

element.name: dateOfCatchProcessTypeCode
element.definition: The process of how the fish is dated, for example REAL_TIME as fish are caught they are dated and time stamped like tuna, ONE_TIME_CATCH on a date for fish farming, or PERIODIC_CATCH meaning the catch date reflective of seasonal catch like lobster trapping.

element.name: organicClaimAgencyTypeCode
element.definition: A code depicting whether an organic agency manages organic standards or issues certifications.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: contextIdentification
element.definition: The unique identifier established for the business context established by GS1.

element.name: lastChangedDateTime
element.definition: Date assigned by system indicating last time the information was changed. This date is generic and will be stored where assigned and will accompany every message.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: codeListVersion
element.definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

element.name: nestingIncrement
element.definition: Indicates the incremental height of Trade Items nested together. In the case of two garbage cans nested together, this would be the height between the lip of the lower can and the lip on the upper can.

element.name: effectiveEndDateTime
element.definition: A date\time used to indicate when the component depicted in the segment is no longer available for use.

element.name: gpcAttributeTypeName
element.definition: The GS1 provided text equivalent of the Global Product Classification Attribute Code.

element.name: foodBeverageCompositionDescription
element.definition: A text description of either the associated value or the actual database entry lookup for example chicken soup clear instant.

element.name: maximumBatteryLife
element.definition: The maximum capacity of the battery, before it decreases with time and usage. It should be associated to the Battery Type in case a trade item has 2 different types of batteries. The different batteries could have different battery life.

element.name: isActiveDevice
element.definition: Indication if the Basic UDI-DI (Global Model Number) is an Active device. 'Active' means any device, the operation of which depends on a source of energy other than that generated by the human body for that purpose, or by gravity, and which acts by changing the density of or converting that energy. Devices intended to transmit energy, substances or other elements between an active device and the patient, without any significant change, shall not be deemed to be active devices. Software shall also be deemed to be an active device.

element.name: workingPressureRatingMaximum
element.definition: The maximum approved working pressure rating for the product for a specific medium state (water, gas, etc).

element.name: doesTradeItemContainNoncreditableGrains
element.definition: An indication that the item contains non-creditable grains. The existence of non-creditable grains in excess of specified limits may alter the item’s credit toward child nutrition requirements as specified by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body.

element.name: isProhibitedForTransportation
element.definition: Indicates whether an item is prohibited for transportation via a specified mode.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: lethalConcentration50MeasurementPrecision
element.definition: The measurement precision used to determine the lethal concentration 50 for example EXACT.

element.name: quantityOfChildren
element.definition: Value indicates the number of unique next lower level trade items contained in a complex trade item. A complex trade item can contain at least 2 different GTINs.

element.name: globalWarmingPotentialEquivalentBasisYearsCode
element.definition: The time perspective over which global warming potential is considered (20, 100, 500 years). Use the characterization factors of the 4<sup>th</sup> assessment report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). A 100 year time perspective is recommended. The time perspective chosen should always be communicated together with the metric.

element.name: minimumAmountOfAnimalProtein
element.definition: Indicate the minimum amount of animal meat (or poultry) protein contained in the product. The determination of this is made by the supplier and may be subject to target market regulations or trade organization guidelines.

element.name: regulatedChemicalSunsetDateTime
element.definition: As the date from which the placing on the market and the use of a substance is prohibited or restricted.

element.name: creditableGrainAmountPerPortion
element.definition: The gram per portion value of the creditable grains contained in the trade item as specified on the Product Formulation Statement and defined by the requirements, rules and regulations set forth by the applicable product formulation statement regulatory body.

element.name: sourceDataPool
element.definition: A data pool that supports the functionality required by a Data Source such as Data Loading, Publication, Notification, Registration, etc.

element.name: nonhazardousWasteDescription
element.definition: A classification of non-hazardous waste managed at the federal or state level for example a code for disposal of latex paint.

element.name: growingMethodCode
element.definition: Note: This attribute is being deprecated in a future release. Use growingMethodCode in GrowingMethodInformation class in the same module. The code indicating how the product has been grown, cultivated, reared and/or raised.

element.name: registrationDate
element.definition: The date the party was registered in the Global Registry

element.name: logisticsUnitCubeDimension
element.definition: The dimensions of an imaginary cube which can be drawn around both the unit load (content) and the platform upon which the goods are carried if there is one, as defined in the formula of H X W X D (the linear dimensions multiplied to get a cubic result).

element.name: rawMaterialIrradiatedCode
element.definition: Indicates if radiation has been applied to a trade item’s raw material.

element.name: bitternessOfBeerMeasurement
element.definition: Indicates the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the bitterness of beer, expressed in IBU and/or EBU .

element.name: criteriaJoinType
element.definition: A code that allows adjacent (as defined by Search Criteria Sequence) Search Criteria logic to be linked by adding (AND) or providing more options (OR).

element.name: yearOfProduction
element.definition: The year during which the film was produced.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: nutrientValueDerivationCode
element.definition: The derivation of the values, percent of intake and quantity contained, provided in the nutrient class.

element.name: priceValueQualifier
element.definition: A code assigned to identify the basis on which a specific price value is acted upon. For example, if the Price Value was 2%, the Price Value Qualifier would be ‘percent’.

element.name: toxicityReferenceSubstanceCode
element.definition: The reference substance or unit which is used to represent cancerous toxicity effects.

element.name: nameTypeCode
element.definition: Indicates the type of the name

element.name: countrySubdivisionCode
element.definition: The country subdivision in which a processing or other activity has been performed for example processing, bottling, manufacturing.

element.name: dutyFeeTaxRate
element.definition: The current tax or duty rate percentage applicable to the trade item.

element.name: hazardStatementsDescription
element.definition: A description of standard phrases assigned to a hazard class and category that describe the nature of the hazard..

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: creditableIngredientDescription
element.definition: A description of the trade item's creditable ingredient applicable to the creditable ingredient type and as noted on the Product Formulation Statement. In the US, this description should be from the Food Buying Guide or an Alternate Protein Product letter (APP) or a Child Nutrition Source Label.

element.name: quantityOfNextLowerLevelTradeItem
element.definition: The number of one child trade item (as identified by the association of ChildTradeItem class to TradeItemIdentification class) contained by the parent trade item. The child trade item must be in the hierarchy level immediately below the parent trade item.

element.name: amountPerUnit
element.definition: Allowance/charge per unit expressed as an amount.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: upperExplosiveLimit
element.definition: The high end value expressed as a percent by volume that the product will still explode.

element.name: dangerousGoodsTechnicalName
element.definition: Provides the dangerous goods technical information.

element.name: dexterityUsageCode
element.definition: A code describing the type of handedness the trade item is designed to be used for example LEFT_HANDED, RIGHT_HANDED, etc.

element.name: targetConsumerAge
element.definition: Identifies the target consumer age range for which a trade item has been designed.

element.name: fatPercentageInDryMatterMeasurementPrecisionCode
element.definition: A code qualifying the percentage of fat in dry matter, for example LESS_THAN

element.name: multiComponentDeviceTypeCode
element.definition: The device is either a system which is a device in itself, a procedure pack which is a device in itself or kit (only applicable in case of IVDR Devices). This is a applicable for standard devices (not systems or procedure packs). For example in the EU (in accordance with the Art. 22(4) MDR).

element.name: functionalBasisUnitCode
element.definition: Code of the functional basis unit.

element.name: numberOfFacilitiesInStressedWaterArea
element.definition: The number of facilities involved with the production of packaging materials (including recycled materials), packaging constituents, packaging components or units of packaging and/or filling and sealing of units of packaging that operate in areas identified as stressed or scarce fresh water resource area.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: editionNumber
element.definition: The number of a numbered edition. Optional and non-repeating. Normally sent only for the second and subsequent editions of a work, but by agreement between parties to an ONIX exchange a first edition may be explicitly numbered.

element.name: pillowShapeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the shape of a pillow.

element.name: recommendedUsageLocation
element.definition: The primary location recommended for the item's use for example indoor, outdoor, indoor/outdoor, vehicle, kitchen, etc.

element.name: isTradeItemNonphysical
element.definition: An indicator that the trade item is not a physical item and as such has no dimensional manifestation. For example a computer download of software, movies or music, a service agreement, or prepaid cellular time.

element.name: firstAidProceduresDescription
element.definition: A description of any first aid procedures necessary in case of exposure. Note: This is used in compliance with ADR (European Agreement concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road).

element.name: attributeCode
element.definition: The value associated with the codeListName for example MLT for MEASUREMENT_CODE.

element.name: deviceSubStatusStartDateTime
element.definition: The date time when the sub-status of the medical device begins for the EU Market.

element.name: fileLifestyleDescription
element.definition: The lifestyles to which this digital asset can be used. For example psychographic, demographic, age, etc.

element.name: clinicalSizeTypeCode
element.definition: The qualifier to denote the dimensional size which is clinically relevant for the use of the trade item by the clinical user. For example "NEEDLE_GAUGE" for a 16 gauge needle, or "VOLUME" for a 200 cc syringe.

element.name: minimumOptimumConsumptionTemperature
element.definition: The lower limit drinking temperature of the optimum range of the drinking temperature. The optimum range of the drinking temperature is a recommendation and is based on the experience of the individual producer.

element.name: feedAdditiveStatement
element.definition: List of the substances added to feed during processing, as for preservation, coloring, or stabilization as governed by local rules and regulations.

element.name: publishingStatusCode
element.definition: Identifies the status of a published product

element.name: postConsumerRecycledContentPercentage
element.definition: Indicates the percentage of post-consumer material used in the trade item. The post-consumer material is collected from recycle bins and used as pulp to make new items. The percentage of post-consumer material is needed to drive whether the recycled logo goes on the item. Some post-consumer material is collected from the recycle bins and used as pulp to make new items.

element.name: numberOfIllustrations
element.definition: The number of illustrations or other content items of the type specified. Optional and non-repeating.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: juiceContentPercent
element.definition: The fruit juice content of the trade item expressed as a percentage.

element.name: codeListVersion
element.definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

element.name: communicationChannelName
element.definition: The name of a specific communication channel for example Facebook, Twitter, etc.

element.name: nonfoodIngredientCodeReference
element.definition: A code from a specific code list for a nonFood ingredient.

element.name: materialPercentage
element.definition: Net weight percentage of a product material of the first main material. The percent-ages must add up to 100.

element.name: targetSkinTypeCode
element.definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify different types of skin the product is intended for.

element.name: certificationIdentification
element.definition: A reference issued to confirm that something has passed certification.

element.name: sleeveType
element.definition: A free text description of the garment sleeve type.

element.name: alcoholProof
element.definition: Alcohol proof is a measure of how much ethanol (alcohol) is contained in an alcoholic beverage.

element.name: maximumAvailableStorageCapacity
element.definition: The maximum data storage capacity available within the trade item for electronic file storage hardware.

element.name: rEACHChemicalRegistrationNumber
element.definition: A unique registration number for a chemical for a company. This is issued by the European Chemical Agency (ECHA) and is unique per chemical.

element.name: mountLocationDescription
element.definition: A description of how the item is mounted for use especially with shelves for example on the wall, ceiling or floor.

element.name: shippingContainerQuantityDescription
element.definition: The quantity of the contents of the shipping container as described on the outside of the shipping container, for example 100 .5 oz envelopes.

element.name: fileVersion
element.definition: A description of the terms used by the manufacturer to denote the version of the digital asset.

element.name: maximumTemperature
element.definition: Specifies the upper limit of the temperature range.

element.name: ingredientOfConcernCode
element.definition: Indicates a claim to an ingredient, considered to be a concern for regulatory or other reasons, and which is “contained” within the trade item but may not need to specify the amount whether approximate, or an accurate measurement be given.

element.name: controlOfHazardousSubstancesRegulationsAgency
element.definition: The government or agency that owns regulation controlling hazard substances that may apply to the product.

element.name: lethalDose50
element.definition: Lethal Dose 50 is a statistically derived single dose that can be expected to cause death in 50% of the test animals when administered by the route indicated (oral, dermal, inhalation). It is expressed as a weight of substance per unit weight of animal, e.g., mg/kg.

element.name: childNutritionQualifierCode
element.definition: A qualifier to specify the type of equivalent measurement that is applicable to the item as specified in the child nutrition statement or label. Example: FRUIT_VEGETABLE_OR_FRUIT_VEGETABLE_ALTERNATIVE.

element.name: containerTypeCode
element.definition: The container in which the alcohol product has undergone a specific process. Example: Bourbon, Beer, Sherry Butt, Pin (Cask).

element.name: packagingComponentDescription
element.definition: Part of packaging that can be separated by hand or by using simple physical means (EN 13427, ISO/DIS 18601), for example a packaging film.

element.name: productYield
element.definition: Product quantity after preparation.

element.name: lightBulbFilamentTypeCode
element.definition: The type of filament used in the light bulb. A filament is the threadlike conductor, often of tungsten, in the bulb that is heated to incandescence by the passage of current.

element.name: importClassificationTypeCode
element.definition: Imports and exports of trade items typically require classification codes to determine appropriate duties and tariffs. Values include Netherlands Import Code, Harmonized Commodity Description and Coding System, Customs Tariff and INTRASTAT Code, Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States, INTRASTAT Combined Nomenclature, Tarif Intégré de la Communauté

element.name: audioVisualMediaItemContributorTypeCode
element.definition: A code identifying the type of contributor to media content for example artist, producer, director.

element.name: authorisationDateTime
element.definition: First day on which the item will be authorised for sale to a location.

element.name: lightBulbWarmUpTime
element.definition: Indicates the maximum time in seconds the light bulb is warmed up to 60% of the full light output.

element.name: isTradeItemShippedInMultipleContainers
element.definition: Indicates that more than one box is to be delivered when the trade item is ordered.

element.name: documentActionCode
element.definition: Code specifying the action to be taken in the system of the recipient using the information in the document.

element.name: acidificationMeasurementReferenceSubstanceDescription
element.definition: The reference substance description used to represent the potential to acidify ecosystems.

element.name: registrationAgency
element.definition: An agency that issues registration numbers for any item or substance for example a chemical that is contained within the product.

element.name: recommendedFrequencyOfFeeding
element.definition: How frequently it is recommended to feed an animal the quantity of feed within a time period for the specified feed life-stage. Examples: 2 feedings per day, maximum 2 chew sticks and/or 2 portions per day.

element.name: isTradeItemADisplayUnit
element.definition: An indicator whether or not a trade item is or could be used as a display unit. A display unit is intended to be shipped to a store without being split at a distribution centre or similar party and is intended to be displayed in a retail store either on a shelf or on the shop floor.

element.name: declaredPower
element.definition: The declared power of a light bulb defines how much electricity the bulb can transform into light and heat over a given amount of time. If left on for one hour, a 25 Watt light bulb will use 25 Watt-hours (Wh) of energy.

element.name: languageCode
element.definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

element.name: storageCompatibilityCode
element.definition: A storage compatibilities expressed as a code.

element.name: noncreditableGrainDescription
element.definition: A descriptive term to describe the non creditable grain contained in the item. This value must be supplied when non-creditable grains are present in the trade item. In the US, this description should be from the Food Buying Guide.

element.name: countrySubdivisionCode
element.definition: The country subdivision in which a processing or other activity has been performed for example processing, bottling, manufacturing.

element.name: additionalCameraAngleCode
element.definition: An additional camera angle used to take a picture of the trade item for example ZOOM_VIEW. If this attribute is not populated, the assumption is a full trade item view. Uses FileCameraPerspectiveCode code list.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: <font color="#ff0000">Attribute value pair information.</font>

element.name: propertyCode
element.definition: A property of a classification of an item expressed as a code.

element.name: relevantSupportingSubstanceHazardousDocumentation
element.definition: This is a certificate of compliance with relevant legislation. So the metric is a simple yes qualified with supporting documentation or a no.

element.name: hatTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the form or style of a hat.

element.name: chemicalPropertyName
element.definition: A characteristic of a chemical substance expressed as a name for example radionuclide.

element.name: audioVisualMediaDateTime
element.definition: The date for audio or visual media products for example release date.

element.name: actionNeeded
element.definition: Identifies the type of action the data source needs to take in order to resolve the data recipient's issue.

element.name: creditableIngredientAmountPerRawPortion
element.definition: The ounces per portion value of the raw creditable fruit or vegetable ingredient contained in the trade item as specified on the Product Formulation Statement and defined by the requirements, rules and regulations set forth by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body.

element.name: bracketRangeQualifierCode
element.definition: Specifies whether the bracket range is based upon an amount, a measurement or another quantity

element.name: compulsoryAdditionalLabelInformation
element.definition: The legally required/compulsory additional label information as stated on the product packaging or label.

element.name: physiochemicalCharacteristicReferenceValue
element.definition: The measured value of the physiochemical characteristic or a value which results of several tests during the production process.

element.name: languageCode
element.definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

element.name: haveYouMinimizedHazardousSubstance
element.definition: Meeting the requirements of EN 13428 or ISO 18602 on heavy metals and dangerous/hazardous substances.

element.name: packagingShapeCode
element.definition: A code depicting the shape of a package for example cone.

element.name: packagingWeightReductionProtocolName
element.definition: The protocol name that the calculation is based on. (i.e. packaging weight reduction should be calculated according to the protocol stipulated in GPPS 2.0)

element.name: regulatoryAgency
element.definition: The required information is the name of the specific entity in charge of issuing the permit to a company.

element.name: height
element.definition: The height of the unit load, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard, including the shipping platform unless it is excluded according to the platformTypeCode chosen.

element.name: fileEffectiveStartDateTime
element.definition: The date upon which the target of this external link begins to be effective for use.

element.name: feedingAmount
element.definition: The amount of feed which is specified for the feed life-stage and qualified by the weight of animal being fed.

element.name: lethalDose50Basis
element.definition: The basis measurement for the measurement of a Lethal Dose for example 1 LT in the ratio 10 MG/1 LT.

element.name: partyEndEffectiveDate
element.definition: The date and time that the party is no longer active.

element.name: dutyFeeTaxTypeCode
element.definition: Identification of the type of duty or tax or fee applicable to the trade item. This will vary by target market.

element.name: maximumFeedingAmount
element.definition: The maximum amount of feed which is specified for the feed life-stage and qualified by the weight of animal being fed.

element.name: storageStateCode
element.definition: A code depicting that the referred product was previously frozen or not.

element.name: startDateTimeOfExclusivity
element.definition: The date and time at which a product starts to be exclusive to a trading partner.

element.name: contributorPlaceRegion
element.definition: Identifies a region with which a contributor is particularly associated

element.name: gpcCategoryCode
element.definition: Code specifying a product category according to the GS1 Global Product Classification (GPC) standard.

element.name: tradeItemDateOnPackagingFormatTypeCode
element.definition: A category of date formats for example calendar or ordinal date.

element.name: professionalAffiliation
element.definition: An organisation to which a contributor to the product was affiliated at the time of its creation

element.name: packagingMaterialDescription
element.definition: A description of the packaging material.

element.name: minimumToleranceTemperature
element.definition: The minimum temperature at which the item is still usable. The tolerated temperature indicates that the temperature of the trade item should never fall below the minimum temperature.

element.name: aquaticEutrophicationReferenceSubstanceDescription
element.definition: The reference substance used to represent aquatic eutrophication potential.

element.name: targetHairTypeCode
element.definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the hair type for which the product is intended.

element.name: usageColourDescription
element.definition: A description of the usage of colour(s) the trade item offers such as pens, markers, ink pads, printer cartridges and other implements that provide color. Examples include black, white.

element.name: multipleContainerQuantity
element.definition: The quantity of containers when the complete trade item is packed in multiple containers. If all components are packed together into one item this attribute is not used. For example: 3 boxes = 1st box has 1 table, 2 more boxes with 2 chairs each, this attribute would contain the value 3.

element.name: catchDateTime
element.definition: The date of the catch within the EDI and/or Information at the label distributed with the product for information of any single lot of fresh fish and seafood product. Format (YYYYMMDD) as a specification with time stamp is not required in the current EU Regulation. This required attribute will help the global retail industry to fulfill the EU requirements for a common fisheries policy. element.name: itemAuthorisationStatusReason

element.name: stackingWeightMaximum

element.name: chemicalIngredientIdentification

element.name: gHSSignalWordsCode

element.name: partyDataPool

element.name: containedAlternativeProteinPercent

element.name: regulationLevelCodeReference
element.definition: An external code associated with a specific warning type and possibly a description that helps recipients identify items of similar levels of warnings, that cannot be obtained from a description. The information provided in this attribute may come from a specific article in the full Regulation. For examples : - if the regulationTypeCode is "SMALL_PARTS" the regulationLevelCodeReference would be “Level 5” with codeDescription “Not for ages under 3” - if the regulationTypeCode is "BIOCIDE_REGULATION" the regulationLevelCodeReference would be “PT1” with codeDescription “Human hygiene”

element.name: allowanceChargeAmount

element.name: tradeItemLicenseOwnerGLN

element.name: isBioengineeredDeclarationClaimRelevantDataProvided
element.definition: All Bioengineered Declaration Claim Information is populated for those values which are relevant or required to be populated on the product label or label equivalent. values not populated are not relevant or not required to be populated on the product label by local regulations.

element.name: grossWeight
element.definition: Used to identify the gross weight of the trade item. The gross weight includes all packaging materials of the trade item. At pallet level the trade item-GrossWeight includes the weight of the pallet itself. For example, "200 grm", value - total pounds, total grams, etc. Has to be asso-ciated with a valid UOM.

element.name: tradeItemLicenseTitle

element.name: shippingRegulationException

element.name: allergenRelevantDataProvidedDateTime

element.name: shippingQuantityMinimum

element.name: contentDateRoleTypeCode

element.name: neckwearTypeCode

element.name: compulsoryAdditionalLabelInformationTypeCode

element.name: complementAddress

For example, an industrial zone or apartment number. Required in case the PD Organisation link is provided (Product Designer Link relates to an Organisation)

element.name: alcoholicPermissionLevel
element.definition: Indication of a Permission level for alcoholic products dependent on the product classification. The permission level codes should reflect those of the target market.

element.name: alternativeName
element.definition: It may be used to send a pseudonym as well as a real name, where both names are on the product, eg to handle such cases as ‘Ian Rankin writing as Jack Harvey’; or to send an authority-controlled form of a name; or to identify the real name of the contributor where the book is written under a pseudonym (and the real identity need not be kept private). element.name: acidificationMeasurementProtocolCode

element.name: targetOccasionOrTheme

element.name: postalCode

element.name: originOfWineCode

element.name: nonfoodIngredientOfConcernCode

element.name: fileRightsDescription
element.definition: The structure for Digital Rights Management (DRM) which is in place on the file. element.name: tradeItemVariantStatement

element.name: chemicalRegulationName

element.name: gpcCategoryCode

element.name: handlingInstructionsCodeReference
element.definition: Defines the information and processes needed to safely handle the trade item.

element.name: conditionActionCode

The Party Receiving Private Data is able to use this code to determine the nature of the action associated with each condition within each condition segment. For example the addition of a new record, the modification of an existing record or the correction of an existing record.

element.name: copyrightOwnerIdentifierTypeCodeReference

element.name: facilitiesInStressedWaterAreaPercent

element.definition: The process the packaging could undertake for recyclable & sustainability programs. Examples COMPOSTABLE, ENERGY_RECOVERABLE, REUSABLE

element.name: collarType

element.name: personNameInverted

element.name: dutyFeeTaxBasis

element.name: waistRiseCode

element.name: hazardousWasteCode

element.name: drugInteractions

element.name: servingSuggestion

element.name: caseDescription
element.definition: Describes the shape and characteristics of the case the trade item will be inside. For example watches come in unique cases. Examples include leather bound case, designer matching case, velvet lined box.

element.name: nutritionalProgramDetail
element.definition: Information providing more detail as to the level or value relevant for the nutritionalProgramCode. For example, 5 points as applicable to the Weight Watchers program. This value should be expressed as text and be as is presented on the item or its packaging.

element.name: editionTypeCode
