element.definition: A rating assigned to the title by a country, industry or volunteer organization that may be of interest or concern to the consumer.

element.name: ratingContentDescriptorCode
element.definition: A code that identifies one or several elements that have triggered a particular rating and/or may be of interest or concern.

element.name: priceEffectiveStartDate
element.definition: This is the effective start date of the price agreed to by the trading partners. This start date is mandatory and, if no end date is communicated, then implies that the price is effective until further notice. Various types of dates may be pre-aligned between buyer and seller. For example, based upon a prior agreement between trading partners this date may relate to any of the following events, first order date, first ship date, and first arrival date.

element.name: priceEffectiveEndDate
element.definition: The effective end date of the price is optional based upon the agreement by the trading partners. If an invalid end date is communicated, then it is implied that the price and its effective date are effective until further notice. Examples of invalid dates include 99/99/9999, 00/00/0000, blank, etc. These invalid end dates should not be communicated. Various types of dates may be pre-aligned between buyer and seller. For example, based upon a prior agreement between trading partners this date may relate to any of the following events, last order date, last ship date, and last arrival date.

element.name: priceBasisQuantity
element.definition: The price basis quantity is the associated quantity of trade item for which a price is given.

element.name: dateDue
element.definition: Calendar date specifying when the payment is due.

element.name: dayOfMonthDue
element.definition: The time at which a payment is due, expressed as a day of the month.

element.name: communicationChannelCode
element.definition: Code specifying the type of communication channel, for example TELEPHONE.

element.name: communicationValue
element.definition: Text identifying the endpoint for the communication channel, for example a telephone number or an e-mail address.

element.name: city
element.definition: Text specifying the name of the city.

element.name: countryCode
element.definition: Code specifying the country for the address.

element.name: languageOfThePartyCode
element.definition: Code specifying the language of an addressed party.

element.name: name
element.definition: The name of the party expressed in text.

element.name: cityCode
element.definition: Identifier for a city, expressed as a short code rather than the full name

element.name: countyCode
element.definition: A code that identifies a county. A county is a territorial division in some countries, forming the chief unit of local administration. In the US, a county is a political and administrative division of a state.

element.name: crossStreet
element.definition: A street intersecting a main street (usually at right angles) and continuing on both sides of it

element.name: currencyOfPartyCode
element.definition: Code specifying the currency of an addressed party.

element.name: pOBoxNumber
element.definition: The number that identifies a PO box. A PO box is a box in a post office or other postal service location assigned to an organization where postal items may be kept.

element.name: postalCode
element.definition: Text specifying the postal code for an address.

element.name: provinceCode
element.definition: Text specifying a province in abbreviated format.

element.name: state
element.definition: One of the constituent units of a nation having a federal government.

element.name: streetAddressOne
element.definition: The first free form line of an address. This first part is printed on paper as the first line below the name. For example, the name of the street and the number in the street or the name of a building.

element.name: streetAddressTwo
element.definition: The second free form line of an address. This second part is printed on paper as the second line below the name. The second free form line complements the first free form line to locate the party e.g. floor number, name of a building, suite number or

element.name: latitude
element.definition: Angular distance North or South from the earth’s equator measured through 90 degrees.

element.name: longitude
element.definition: The arc or portion of the earth’s equator intersected between the meridian of a given place and the prime meridian and expressed either in degrees or in time.

element.name: aDRDangerousGoodsLimitedQuantitiesCode
element.definition: A code defined by RID (Regulations concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Rail) and ADR (Accord Européen Relatif au Transport International des Marchandises Dangereuses par Route) specifying whether a dangerous good can be packaged in small quantities providing they are packaged and labelled in accordance with certain requirements. Note: this attribute is being deprecated for release 3.1.8. Use dangerousGoodsLimitedQuantitiesCode.

element.name: dangerousGoodsRegulationCode
element.definition: An indication of the classification system(s) of dangerous goods and/or the Agency(ies) responsible for it.

element.name: hazardousMaterialAdditionalInformation
element.definition: Any regulatory information required that is not specifically identified by another field.

element.name: classOfDangerousGoods
element.definition: The dangerous goods classification of the trade item. Dangerous classes explain in general terms the hazardous nature and properties of the goods and serves to classify them together in terms of their most significant risk.

element.name: dangerousGoodsClassificationCode
element.definition: A classification code of the trade item (dangerous goods) for transport by road and rail for example ADR/RID. It indicates the dangerous characteristics respectively the subsections of the trade item within a given classification.

element.name: dangerousGoodsHazardousCode
element.definition: Dangerous goods hazard ID number, which must be applied to the vehicle, when transporting this trade item (dangerous good) by road or rail, to inform the police, the fire brigade and others in case of an accident about the kind of danger caused by the cargo.

element.name: dangerousGoodsPackingGroup
element.definition: Identifies the degree of risk these dangerous goods present during transport according to IATA/IMDG/ADR/RID regulations.

element.name: dangerousGoodsShippingName
element.definition: Shipping name of the trade item (dangerous goods). The recognized agencies (see dangerousGoodsRegulationsCodes), in their regulations, provide a list of all acceptable proper shipping names.

element.name: dangerousGoodsSpecialProvisions
element.definition: A numeric code of special regulations to be met regarding a Dangerous Goods Classification Regulation. For example ADR 2005 provides additional information for identifying the substances or items (s. 3.2.1 ADR 2005). Special provisions can include transport restrictions, exemptions from regulation, explanations on the classifying of certain forms of the dangerous goods in question as well as additional marking and labelling requirements.

element.name: netMassOfExplosives
element.definition: The measurement of the net explosive mass of the trade item (dangerous goods) for transport by road and rail according to a dangerous goods classification regulation.

element.name: unitedNationsDangerousGoodsNumber
element.definition: The four-digit number assigned by the United Nations Committee of Experts on the Transport of Dangerous Goods to classify a substance or a particular groups of substances. Abbreviation: UNDG Number. Recommend to use codes listed in the latest edition of the UN Recommendations on the Transport of Dangerous Goods.

element.name: dangerousHazardousLabelNumber
element.definition: A visible number indicating the specific risk and thus the required precautions associated with a dangerous or hazardous good for example, the indication of the hazardous label number according to chapter 3.2, table A of the ADR.

element.name: dangerousHazardousLabelSequenceNumber
element.definition: A sequence number indicating the primacy of one dangerous/hazardous label number over another. For example, a value of 1 would indicate that the associated hazard label number is the primary, 2 = secondary, etc.

element.name: currencyConversionFromCode
element.definition: ISO Code for the currency from which an amount is converted

element.name: currencyConversionToCode
element.definition: ISO Code for the currency to which an amount is converted

element.name: exchangeRate
element.definition: The price of one currency in terms of another, that is, the number of units of one currency that may be exchanged for one unit of another currency.

element.name: exchangeRateDateTime
element.definition: The date as of which the currency exchange rate is valid.

element.name: canFileStream
element.definition: An indicator that the digital asset is compressed to start displaying/running before fully uncompressing.

element.name: fileAspectRatio
element.definition: A description of the aspect ratio used to determine how a digital asset fits on a page or monitor.

element.name: fileColourSchemeCode
element.definition: The type of colour scheme used in the digital asset.

element.name: fileContrast
element.definition: The contrast used in the digital asset. Contrast is the difference in brightness between light and dark areas of an image. Contrast determines the number of shades in the image.

element.name: fileName
element.definition: The name of the file that contains the external information.

element.name: filePixelHeight
element.definition: The number of pixels along the vertical axis of the image.

element.name: filePixelWidth
element.definition: The number of pixels along the horizontal axis of the image.

element.name: filePlaybackRate
element.definition: The targeted frame rate for the display of the digital asset, expressed as an integer representing the number of frames per second.

element.name: fileResolutionDescription
element.definition: The resolution of the file. Knowing the resolution will allow the user to be able to determine the best system with which to utilize the file.

element.name: fileRunTime
element.definition: The playback or running length of time for the digital asset. This most common is in reference to video or audio files, but is not limited to them. This would be expressed in hours, minutes and second (hh:mm:ss).

element.name: isFileBackgroundTransparent
element.definition: An indicator of whether or not the background used in the file is transparent. Having a transparent background would allow a recipient to place the file into any setting necessary.

element.name: areFeesRequiredForUse
element.definition: An indicator whether or not a fee is required for the use of this digital asset.

element.name: canFilesBeEdited
element.definition: An indicator of whether the user or recipient of the digital asset can edit it prior to use or as a function of using the asset. Some digital assets are designed such that the recipient can edit the asset to meet the needs of a final output.

element.name: intendedPublicationCountryCode
element.definition: The country/countries in which the digital asset is designed to be used.

element.name: isFileForInternalUseOnly
element.definition: An indicator whether or not the file is intended for internal use only and not for general publication.

element.name: isTalentReleaseOnFile
element.definition: An indicator whether or not the owner of the asset has a talent release on file. This applies to files where talent or a model is used.

element.name: areHumanModelsInFile
element.definition: An indicator whether or not the item is shown or depicted with human models.

element.name: fileAuthorName
element.definition: The organization(s) or person(s) who is responsible for creating the digital asset.

element.name: fileLanguageCode
element.definition: The specified language to which the digital asset is targeted.

element.name: fileLayerQuantity
element.definition: The number of layers in the digital asset.

element.name: fileItemPositionCode
element.definition: A description of how the item is placed in the digital asset for example the item is propped (leaning against an object) or held (being held by a model).

element.name: itemDepictionTypeCode
element.definition: The state of the item as it is being depicted in the digital assets for example gift wrapped or assembled.

element.name: numberOfItemsInDigitalAsset
element.definition: The number of items in the digital asset, where the asset contains more than one item.

element.name: financialRoutingNumber
element.definition: Number assigned to a transaction in financial routing between parties. The number is determined by and used in conjunction with the type of routing, e.g. SWIFT,ABA,CHIPS.

element.name: financialRoutingNumberTypeCode
element.definition: Code specifying the type of financial routing, e.g. SWIFT.

element.name: financialAccountNumberTypeCode
element.definition: Identifies the type of financial account number.

element.name: financialAccountNumber
element.definition: Text specifying the number of the financial account.

element.name: partyRoleCode
element.definition: A code that identifies the role of a party in a business transaction.

element.name: date
element.definition: The specification of a day as calendar date.

element.name: time
element.definition: The specification of a point in time during the day.

element.name: dataSource
element.definition: Entity that provides the global data synchronization network with Master Data. The Data Source is officially recognized as the owner of this data. For a given Item or Party, the source of data is responsible for permanent updates of the information under its responsibility.

element.name: gtin
element.definition: A particular Global trade item Number, a numerical value used to uniquely identify a trade item. A trade item is any trade item (trade item or service) upon which there is a need to retrieve pre-defined information and that may be planned, priced, ordered, delivered and or invoiced at any point in any supply chain.

element.name: targetMarketCountryCode
element.definition: The code that identifies the target market. The target market is at country level or higher geographical definition and is where a trade item is intended to be sold.

element.name: targetMarketSubdivisionCode
element.definition: The Code for country sub-division definition used to indicate the geo-political subdivision of the target market (=country ).

element.name: dutyFeeTaxCategoryCode
element.definition: Depicts the applicability of the tax rate or amount for a trade item for example zero, low or exempt.

element.name: incotermCode
element.definition: Incoterms is an abbreviation for International Commercial Terms. The International Chamber of Commerce created and manages the Incoterms and their definitions. There are 13 available for use in the buyer-seller contractual agreements.

element.name: incotermCodeLocation
element.definition: A description of the location required by an Incoterm.

element.name: referenceDocumentIdentifier
element.definition: Identifier that provides a link to further detail on the price condition, for example an associated contract between trading partners.

element.name: referenceDocumentDescription
element.definition: A free form text field used to describe a contract or other document which contains more information about agreements made regarding a condition.

element.name: performanceRequirementDescription
element.definition: A string of characters used to describe additional or more specific requirements to be met in order to receive a monetary value.

element.name: isTradeItemSeasonal
element.definition: An indicator whether or not the trade item is only offered during certain parts of the year or targeted to different seasons.

element.name: productRange
element.definition: A name, used by a BrandOwner, that span multiple consumer categories or uses. E.g. (Waist Watchers).

element.name: tradeItemFormDescription
element.definition: The physical form or shape of the product. Used, for example, in pharmaceutical industry to indicate the formulation of the trade item. Defines the form the trade item takes and is distinct from the form of the packaging.

element.name: brandDistributionTypeCode
element.definition: Any restrictions imposed on the Trade Item on how it can be sold to the consumer or recipient trading partner.

element.name: tradeItemTradeChannelCode
element.definition: A grouping of entities by common business model concentration used to define the distribution or marketing segmentation of products, customers and geographic areas into common groups that are supplied, serviced and measured in similar ways.

element.name: contactTypeCode
element.definition: The general category of the contact party for a trade item for example Purchasing.

element.name: availableTime
element.definition: The time that a specific contact for a Trade Item is available for contact.

element.name: hasBatchNumber
element.definition: Indication whether the base trade item is batch or lot number requested by law, not batch or lot number requested by law but batch or lot number allocated, or not batch or lot number allocated. A batch or lot number is a manufacturer assigned code used to identify a trade item's trade item on batch or lot. Differs from Serial Number which is a manufacturer assigned code during the trade item on cycle to identify a unique trade item.

element.name: isNonSoldTradeItemReturnable
element.definition: Indicates that the buyer can return the articles that are not sold. Used, for example; with magazines and bread. This is a y/n (Boolean) where y equals right of return. This is at least relevant to General Merchandise, Publishing industries and for some FMCG trade item.

element.name: isTradeItemMarkedAsRecyclable
element.definition: Trade item has a recyclable indication marked on it. This may be a symbol from one of many regional agencies.

element.name: sDSSheetNumber
element.definition: Manufacturer's identification number for the safety data sheet for a trade item.

element.name: isTradeItemPackedIrregularly
element.definition: Indicates that the item is packed in a non-rectilinear pattern such that it is not meaningful to send the number of child trade items in the width/depth/height.

element.name: quantityOfCompleteLayersContainedInATradeItem
element.definition: The number of layers of the base trade item found in a trade item. Does not apply to the base trade item unit.

element.name: quantityOfInnerPack
element.definition: Indicates the number of non-GTIN assignedinner-packs of next lower level trade items within the current GTIN level.

element.name: quantityOfLayersPerPallet
element.definition: The number of layers that a pallet contains. Only used if the pallet has no GTIN. It indicates the number of layers that a pallet contains, according to supplier or retailer preferences.

element.name: quantityOfNextLevelTradeItemWithinInnerPack
element.definition: Indicates the number of next lower level trade items contained within the physical non-GTIN assigned each or inner-packs (inner-pack).

element.name: quantityOfTradeItemsContainedInACompleteLayer
element.definition: The number of trade items contained in a complete layer of a higher packaging configuration. Used in hierarchical packaging structure of a trade item. Cannot be used for trade item base unit.

element.name: quantityOfTradeItemsPerPallet
element.definition: The number of trade items contained in a pallet. Only used if the pallet has no GTIN. It indicates the number of trade items placed on a pallet according to supplier or retailer preferences.

element.name: quantityOfTradeItemsPerPalletLayer
element.definition: The number of trade items contained on a single layer of a pallet. Only used if the pallet has no GTIN. It indicates the number of trade items placed on a pallet layer according to supplier or retailer preferences.

element.name: orderingUnitOfMeasure
element.definition: The alternate Unit of Measure of how Trade Items are ordered by the Retailer under one Unit of Measure, but sold under another Unit of Measure.

element.name: sellingUnitOfMeasure
element.definition: Describes the measurement used for selling unit of the Trade Item to the end consumer. A Trade Item may have only one Unit of Measure.

element.name: securityTagLocationCode
element.definition: This is a code to indicate where the EAS tag is located on the Trade Item. Values include On outside of Trade Item, Concealed inside Trade Item, Integrated Inside Trade Item.

element.name: securityTagTypeCode
element.definition: This is a code to indicate the type of EAS tag located on the Trade Item. Values include Acousto-Magnetic, Electro-Magnetic, Ink or dye, Microwave, Radio Frequency.

element.name: isTradeItemACombinationItem
element.definition: An indicator whether a product assigned with one GTIN contains components which could have different tax rates for example chocolate eggs with toys would be chocolate 7% and toy 19%.

element.name: serialNumberLocationCode
element.definition: The location on the item or packaging of a serial number. A serial number is a code, numeric or alphanumeric, assigned to an individual instance of an entity for its lifetime for example a Microscope model AC-2 with serial number 1234568 and microscope model AC-2 with serial number 1234569.

element.name: degreeOfOriginalWort
element.definition: Specification of the degrees of original wort.

element.name: ingredientIrradiatedCode
element.definition: Indicates if radiation has been applied to a trade item’s ingredient.

element.name: irradiatedCode
element.definition: Indicates if radiation has been applied.

element.name: nonMarkedTradeItemComponents
element.definition: This attribute indicates a non-saleable part of the trade item. It is used to specify components of a trade item that cannot be sold separately. Note: This attribute will be deleted in a future release and should not be used.

element.name: numberOfPackagesForSetPiecesGTIN
element.definition: The total number of separately packaged components comprising a single trade item.

element.name: numberOfPiecesInSet
element.definition: The total quantity of components included in this trade item: E.g: for a 12 pack of yogurt (Vanilla, Chocolate and Strawberry), this would be 12.

element.name: doesItemComeWithHanger
element.definition: A boolean value that indicates whether or not the trade item comes with a hanger.

element.name: isTradeItemHanging
element.definition: An indicator whether or not the trade Item is shipped hanging, as opposed to being shipped with a hanger but not actually hanging.

element.name: standardTypeHangerAgencyCode
element.definition: A code that identifies the agency that specifies industry standards for hangers.

element.name: ageRangeDescription
element.definition: Note: This attribute is being deprecated in a future release. Use targetConsumerAge from TargetConsumer class in MarketingInformationModule. Description of the recommended age range of participating players.

element.name: maximumNumberOfPlayers
element.definition: Maximum number of players that can participate in the game.

element.name: maximumAge
element.definition: Note: This attribute is being deprecated in a future release. Use targetConsumerUsageTypeCode with the value AGE and targetConsumerMaximumUsage from TargetConsumerUsage class in MarketingInformationModule. Recommended oldest age for a game or publication.

element.name: minimumNumberOfPlayers
element.definition: Minimum number of players that can participate in the game.

element.name: minimumAge
element.definition: Note: This attribute is being deprecated in a future release. Use targetConsumerUsageTypeCode with the value AGE and targetConsumerMinimumUsage from TargetConsumerUsage class in MarketingInformationModule. Recommended youngest age for a game or publication.

element.name: batteryTypeCode
element.definition: Type of battery required to operate the game. If “Are Batteries Required” or if “Quantity of Batteries" is populated or if "Are Batteries Included = “Yes” this attribute is required.

element.name: requiredStorageCapacity
element.definition: The required data storage capacity required of the system to store the software.

element.name: requiredHardwarePerformance
element.definition: The hardware performance required of the system to operate the software defined by the fundamental rate in cycles per second measured in hertz.

element.name: requiredSystemMemoryCapacity
element.definition: The temporary system memory capacity required of the system to run the software.

element.name: requiredVideoMemoryCapacity
element.definition: The video memory capacity required of the system to run the software expressed in megabytes. Video memory is memory dedicated to the purpose of holding the information necessary for a graphics card.

element.name: systemRequirementsQualifierCode
element.definition: A code that determines the type of system performance requirements for example minimum or recommended.

element.name: distributionMediaCount
element.definition: The quantity of media storage devices that are included in the package for the purposes of storing the software.

element.name: distributionMediaTypeCode
element.definition: The type of media storage devices that are included in the package for the purposes of storing the software for example memory sticks, discs, cartridges.

element.name: isEligibleForRevenueShare
element.definition: A boolean that indicates if the film is available for revenue share or not.

element.name: boxOfficeRevenueDomestic
element.definition: The revenue the film earned on the target market expressed in local currency.

element.name: boxOfficeRevenueFirstWeekDomestic
element.definition: The revenue the film earned on the target market for the first week expressed in local currency.

element.name: boxOfficeRevenueUS
element.definition: The revenue the film earned on the US market expressed in US dollars.

element.name: boxOfficeRevenueWorldwideUSDollars
element.definition: The revenue the film earned on all the markets expressed in US dollars.the revenue the film earned on all the markets expressed in US dollars.

element.name: closedCaptioningCode
element.definition: A code that indicates if the film has closed captions, no closed captions or if this information is unknown.

element.name: originalLanguageCode
element.definition: The code of the language in which the film is released. It is the language spoken on the screen.

element.name: dubbedSubtitledCode
element.definition:
A code that indicates if the film is dubbed, subtitled or dubbed and subtitled. Subtitled = the film has caption translating dialogue. Dubbed = The film has a translated alternative soundtrack.Dubbed and subtitled = the film has caption to translate dialogue and a translated soundtrack.
Subtitled = the film has caption translating dialogue.
Dubbed = The film has a translated alternative soundtrack.
Dubbed and subtitled = the film has caption to translate dialogue and a translated soundtrack.

element.name: dubbedLanguageCode
element.definition: A code that identifies the dubbed language of a film.

element.name: aspectRatioDescriptionCode
element.definition: A code that indicates the aspect ratio description for example ANAMORPHIC.

element.name: aspectRatioDimensionCode
element.definition: A code that indicates the aspect ratio dimension.

element.name: audioVisualMediaItemContributorName
element.definition: The name of the contributor of the media content for example artist, producer, director.

element.name: cardPriceGroupIdentifier
element.definition: A code that identifies a price.

element.name: trackNumber
element.definition: The number allocated to a disc, beginning with 1.

element.name: trackTime
element.definition: The length of the track expressed in hours and minutes and seconds.

element.name: trackTitle
element.definition: The name of the track or section of the audio visual media trade item.

element.name: discNumber
element.definition: The number allocated to a disc, beginning with 1

element.name: isProductCustomizable
element.definition: Indicates whether the Items that the Retailer markets are customizable to meet the end consumer’s requirements.

element.name: isTradeItemRecalled
element.definition: An indicator for the Trade Item to determine if the Manufacturer or Supplier has recalled the product.

element.name: totalNumberOfComponents
element.definition: The number of different types of components included in this trade item. E.g. for a 12 pack of yogurt (Vanilla, Chocolate and Strawberry) this would be 3.

element.name: componentNumber
element.definition: Indicate a sequence number of a component of a trade item.

element.name: totalRecyclableContentPercentage
element.definition: The percentage of all recycled material used to produce the trade item. Drives whether or not you can describe an item as recycled in advertising/marketing. This is the totalled recycled content including percentage of post consumer recycled. It excludes all packaging material.

element.name: allergenTypeCode
element.definition: Code indicating the type of allergen.

element.name: levelOfContainmentCode
element.definition: Code indicating the level of presence of the allergen.

element.name: ingredientSequence
element.definition: Incremental value (01, 02, 03…) indicating the ingredient order by content percentage of the product. (major ingredient = 01, second ingredient =01.01) etc..

element.name: ingredientCountryOfOriginCode
element.definition: Code indicating the country of origin of the ingredient (ISO-3166).

element.name: ingredientContentPercentage
element.definition: Indication of the percentage of the ingredient contained in the product.

element.name: ingredientCatchZone
element.definition: The sea zone from which the seafood in the trade item was caught in.

element.name: grapeVarietyCode
element.definition: The vine variety used for the production of this wine for example Merlot expressed as a code.

element.name: ingredientGrowingMethodCode
element.definition: The process through which fresh produce is grown and cultivated.

element.name: ingredientPurpose
element.definition: A description of the primary purpose that an ingredient serves for example a colouring in the case of annatto in a cheese rind.

element.name: ingredientSourceAnimalCode
element.definition: The source of raw material used to produce the food product for example a goat for milk.

element.name: microbiologicalOrganismCode
element.definition: Code indicating the type of microbiological organism.

element.name: nutrientTypeCode
element.definition: Code from the list of the INFOODS food component tag names.

element.name: measurementPrecisionCode
element.definition: Code indicating whether the specified nutrient content is exact or approximate.

element.name: dailyValueIntakePercent
element.definition: The percentage of the recommended daily intake of a nutrient as recommended by authorities of the target market. Is expressed relative to the serving size and base daily value intake.

element.name: physiochemicalCharacteristicCode
element.definition: Code indicating the type of physiochemical characteristic.

element.name: productYieldTypeCode
element.definition:
Code indicating the type of yield measurement.
Examples: • After dilution • Drained weight • After cooking • Etc

element.name: productYieldVariationPercentage
element.definition: Indication of range in percent of the given cooking / roasting loss. Percentage that the actual weight of the trade item differs upward or downward from the average or estimated product yield.

element.name: maximumNumberOfSmallestUnitsPerPackage
element.definition: The maximum number of the smallest units contained in the package. This attribute is to be used in conjunction with numberOfSmallestUnitsPerPackage in order to enter a minimum and maximum value. For example for a package of meat balls where the smallest units per package could be from 56-60, the maximumNumberOfSmallestUnitsPerPackage would be 60.

element.name: numberOfServingsPerPackage
element.definition: The total number of servings contained in the package.

element.name: numberOfSmallestUnitsPerPackage
element.definition: The total number of smallest units contained in the product. The smallest unit cannot be further divided without breaking or slicing the product. The smallest units may be uniform or may include a variety of items.

element.name: manufacturerPreparationTypeCode
element.definition: The code specifying the preparation methods the manufacturer has used on the product during the manufacturing process.

element.name: dietTypeCode
element.definition: Code indicating the diet the product is suitable for.

element.name: dietTypeSubcode
element.definition: Indicates a set of agreements or a certificate name that guarantees the product is permitted in a particular diet.

element.name: preparationStateCode
element.definition: Code specifying the preparation state or type the nutrient information applies to, for example, unprepared, boiled, fried.

element.name: preparationTypeCode
element.definition: A code specifying the technique used to make the product ready for consumption. For example: baking, boiling.

element.name: convenienceLevelPercent
element.definition: An indication of the ease of preparation for semi-prepared products. The convenience level indicates the level of preparation in percentage required to prepare and helps the consumer to assess how long it will take to prepare the meal.

element.name: rawMaterialUsedInPreparationWeight
element.definition: The weight of the raw materials (meat) used to produce the finished food product. The weight of the raw materials (for example fat) can differ from the weight of the ingredient in the finished product. In some countries there are legal stipulations that the weight of the raw material used must be indicated if a product is produced using more than 100% of the finished product.

element.name: nutritionalProgramCode
element.definition: Programs designed to encourage people to eat a certain way in order to benefit their nutrition for example “5 a Day”.

element.name: certificationAgency
element.definition: Name of the organization issuing the certification standard or other requirement being met. Free text field. Example: European Union

element.name: certificationStandard
element.definition: The name of the certification standard or the type of certification, e.g. product, process, company, packaging or conformity.

element.name: additiveName
element.definition: The name of any additive or genetic modification contained or not contained in the trade item.

element.name: levelOfContainmentCode
element.definition: Code indicating the level of presence of the additive.

element.name: promotionTypeCode
element.definition: Used to identify the different types of free quantity promotional trade items and the nature of the link between the standard trade item and the promotional trade item.

element.name: regulatoryPermitIdentification
element.definition: Identification of the permit or license given by the regulatory agency.

element.name: permitEndDateTime
element.definition: The date on which the permit expires.

element.name: permitStartDateTime
element.definition: The start date on which the permit is effective.

element.name: doesSaleOfTradeItemRequireGovernmentalReporting
element.definition: Indicates whether the government requires the reporting of sale of the trade item.

element.name: doesTradeItemContainHumanBloodDerivative
element.definition: The use of this attribute indicates that the trade item is a product that contains blood, blood components or blood products used in the manufacturing.

element.name: doesTradeItemContainLatex
element.definition: An indication that the trade item has a positive latex reference on the Trade Item’s labeling?

element.name: isTradeItemConsideredDopingProduct
element.definition: Indicates that the product could be considered a doping substance which is a substance which is part of the list of prohibited substances, pharmaceutical products and methods yearly published by World Anti-Doping Agency. Doping products typically fall into one of the following general types of substances: Anabolic Agents, Hormones and Related Substances, Beta-2 Agonist, Hormone Antagonist and Modulators, Diuretics and other Masking Agents, Stimulants, Narcotics, Cannabinoids, Glucocorticosteroids, Alcohol, Beta-Blockers.

element.name: isTradeItemConsideredGeneric
element.definition: An indication that the trade item is being produced by someone other than the Brand Innovator of the product. A value of no indicates that it is not considered a "Generic Substitution" of another product.

element.name: isTradeItemImplantable
element.definition: Implantable devices are defined as devices that are partly or totally inserted into the human body, as determined by local regulations.

element.name: isTradeItemMarkedNoShake
element.definition: Indicates that the trade item is marked to not be shaken during transport, storage, or use.

element.name: mRICompatibilityCode
element.definition: This is an identification of the compatibility of a trade item for use in the presence of a Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) system.

element.name: externalAgencyName
element.definition: The name of the agency that manages a code list external to GS1.

element.name: externalCodeListName
element.definition: The name of the code list maintained by an agency external to GS1.

element.name: externalCodeListVersion
element.definition: The version of the code list maintained by an agency external to GS1.

element.name: enumerationValue
element.definition: Code List Value maintained by an external code list agency.

element.name: enumerationValueDefinition
element.definition: Definition of the code list value maintained by an external code list agency

element.name: enumerationValueDescription
element.definition: Description of the value in a code list value maintained by an external code list agency. This is primarily used when code list values are sequential numbers.

element.name: manufacturerDeclaredReusabilityTypeCode
element.definition:
Determines if the product is intended for single or multiple uses, including the number of validated cycles and the number of times a product can be used according to the manufacturer specifications.
It is suggested that medical providers consult the device manufacturer’s Instruction For Use (IFU) for full reusability instructions.

element.name: maximumCyclesReusable
element.definition: Maximum number of times this Trade Item can be reused.

element.name: maximumReusableDays
element.definition: The maximum number of days this product can be reused based upon the re-use instructions, local regulations or other manufacturer documentation.

element.name: reuseInstructions
element.definition: Additional instructions that advise the customer on the reusability limitations of this product.

element.name: isTradeItemRequiredToRemainSterile
element.definition: An indication that the products sterile status must be maintained from the point in time of sterilisation until point of administration.

element.name: initialManufacturerSterilisationCode
element.definition: Declaration of sterilisation, including not sterilised, which may have been performed by the manufacturer. Sterilisation refers to any process that effectively kills or eliminates transmissible agents (such as fungi, bacteria, viruses, prions and spore forms etc.) from a surface, equipment, foods, medications, or biological culture medium. Some methods of sterilization are through the application of heat, radiation, and ethylene.

element.name: initialSterilisationPriorToUseCode
element.definition: This is an indication of the type(s) of sterilisation that is required to be completed by a healthcare provider prior to use of the healthcare trade item. Sterilisation refers to any process that effectively kills or eliminates transmissible agents (such as fungi, bacteria, viruses, prions and spore forms etc.) from a surface, equipment, foods, medications, or biological culture medium. Some methods of sterilisation are through the application of heat, radiation, and ethylene.

element.name: manufacturerSpecifiedAcceptableResterilisationCode
element.definition:
This is an indication of the type of acceptable sterilisation that a reusable trade item can undergo by a healthcare provider if a trade item is reusable.
Sterilisation refers to any process that effectively kills or eliminates transmissible agents (such as fungi, bacteria, viruses, prions and spore forms etc.) from a surface, equipment, foods, medications, or biological culture medium. Some methods of sterilisation are through the application of heat, radiation, and ethylene.

element.name: displayScreenTypeCode
element.definition: The type of output device for presentation of visual information.

element.name: horizontalViewingAngle
element.definition: The maximum angle that a picture can be viewed without distortion in the horizontal orientation expressed in degrees.

element.name: verticalViewingAngle
element.definition: The maximum angle that a picture can be viewed without distortion in the vertical orientation expressed in degrees.

element.name: availableBrightnessValues
element.definition: The monitor brightness as a measurement. This is measured in candela per square meter (also known as Nits) or lumens per square meter, and Lux.

element.name: combFilterTechnologyTypeCode
element.definition: A code depiction the type of software allowing the screen to show fine picture detail from channel broadcast or DVD source for example DIGITAL.

element.name: dynamicContrastRatio
element.definition: This is the ratio of luminosity of the brightest and darkest colour the system is capable of producing simultaneously over time. In the attribute the integer given is the first number in the ratio which is always to one, i.e. 550:1.

element.name: multiPictureDisplayCapabilityTypeCode
element.definition: The type of ability to simultaneously display multiple viewing windows on the same screen expressed as a code for example PICTURE_AND_TEXT.

element.name: screenRefreshRate
element.definition: This is defined as the number of times a display's image is repainted or refreshed in per second measured in Hertz.

element.name: staticContrastRatio
element.definition: This is the ratio of luminosity of the brightest and darkest colour the system is capable of producing simultaneously at any instance of time. In the attribute the integer given is the first number in the ratio which is always to one, i.e. 550:1.

element.name: detachableSpeakerTypeCode
element.definition: The type of detachable speakers available on the unit for example wireless.

element.name: fixedSpeakerLocationCode
element.definition: The location of speakers that cannot be detached available on the unit.

element.name: surroundSoundDigitalDecoderTypeCode
element.definition: The type of feature capable of decoding and playback of particular sound systems expressed as a code for example DTS HD.

element.name: totalAudioPowerOutput
element.definition: The total audio power output of the product expressed in Watts.

element.name: audioVisualItemInstallationOptionTypeCode
element.definition: The way that the unit can be mounted or placed expressed as a code for example CEILING_MOUNT.

element.name: vESAWallMountTypeCode
element.definition: The type of VESA wall mount the television is compatible with. VESA is a standard bracket which is a universal mount measured by the Video Electronic Standard Association.

element.name: televisionInformationServiceTypeCode
element.definition: The type of text information services the unit can process expressed as a code for example ANTIOPE.

element.name: televisionTextMemoryPageQuantity
element.definition: This is the quantity of pages expressed as an integer that the television memory maintains for previously viewed Teletext content.

element.name: externalMemoryTypeCode
element.definition: The components, devices, and recording media that retain digital data that is external to the device expressed as a code.

element.name: internalMemoryTypeCode
element.definition: The components, devices, and recording media that retain digital data that is internal to the device expressed as a code.

element.name: availableChannelStationQuantity
element.definition: The number of channels available on the unit expressed as an integer.

element.name: electronicProgrammingGuideDaysAvailable
element.definition: The number of days available in an electronic programming guide expressed as an integer. The electronic programming guide feature is the capability for the users to interact with an intelligent guide.

element.name: signalProcessingTypeCode
element.definition: The type of processing capability of the television to receive and process enhanced signal types expressed as a code for example Analogue.

element.name: tunerTypeCode
element.definition: A tuner type is the technology used for the built-in receiver expressed as a code for example HD (high definition). A tuner receives broadcasts and converts them into signals.

element.name: audioVisualConnectionLocationCode
element.definition: The location on the unit of any audio visual connector for example top.

element.name: audioVisualConnectionQuantity
element.definition: The number of audio visual connections available on the unit expressed as a code.

element.name: audioVisualConnectionTypeCode
element.definition: The types of Standard or Basic Connection Types that are available expressed as a code.

element.name: audioVisualConnectionInputDirectionCode
element.definition: The directions of connections (input, output) that are available expressed as a code value.

element.name: consumerSalesConditionCode
element.definition: A code depicting restrictions imposed on the Trade Item regarding how it can be sold to the consumer for example age restrictions, selling restrictions.

element.name: isDiscountingIllegal
element.definition: An indicator whether or not the product is not legal to discount within a given target market (i.e. the product is subject to government regulation regarding either price floors or pricing practices).

element.name: copyrightFee
element.definition: A fee paid to the content owner for use of the Trade Item or an associated part of the Trade Item.

element.name: copyrightRate
element.definition: A rate paid to the content owner for use of the trade item or an associated part of the trade item.

element.name: materialContent
element.definition: This element is used to indicate the material composition. This element is used in con-junction with the percentage.

element.name: materialPercentage
element.definition: Net weight percentage of a product material of the first main material. The percent-ages must add up to 100.

element.name: descriptiveSizeDimension
element.definition: The textual representation of the size dimension specified by the size type.

element.name: sizeDimension
element.definition: The numerical size measure-ment of the size dimension specified by the size type.

element.name: sizeSystemCode
element.definition: This is the system that is be-ing used to define the size. It is used in conjunction with size group to completely de-fine the size dimension.

element.name: sizeTypeCode
element.definition: The type of size dimension being specified by the size measurement.

element.name: averageDistanceTravelledToPointOfPackagingCode
element.definition: The average distance each packaging material travelled from the packaging material supplier to the point where the product and packaging are combined to form the trade item.

element.name: depositValueEffectiveDateTime
element.definition: First date that the deposit value is valid for the deposit code. CCYYMMDD.

element.name: depositValueEndDateTime
element.definition: Last date that the deposit value in the currency is valid for the deposit code.

element.name: packagingMaterialTypeCode
element.definition: The materials used for the packaging of the trade item for example glass or plastic. This material information can be used by data recipients for: o Tax calculations/fees/duties calculation o Carbon footprint calculations/estimations (resource optimisation) o to determine the material used.

element.name: packagingMaterialLaunchDateTime
element.definition: The first date that a change in packaging material has occurred. This change does not result in a new GTIN at any level of the item hierarchy, such as, an increase or decrease in packaging material and is delivered to the retailer.

element.name: packagingMaterialPerformanceCode
element.definition: A status of packaging performance based on testing to minimize damage to Trade Items for example 3 (improved packaging performance).

element.name: packagingRefundObligationName
element.definition: The refund obligation that the packaging of this item is subject to for example the DPG = Deutsche Pfandsystem GmbH which is a refund obligation for one way beverage packaging for beer, sparkling soft drinks and mineral water.

element.name: packagingRefuseObligationName
element.definition: The name of the specific refuse obligation that may apply to packaging or that the packaging may be exempt from for example ARA.

element.name: packagingTermsAndConditionsCode
element.definition: Indicates if the packaging given in the described packaging configuration is a rented, exchangeable, against deposit or one way/not reusable.

element.name: returnableAssetCapacityContent
element.definition: A measurement of the potential capacity of a returnable asset for example how many bottles can fit into a crate. This is not the content for the full packaging but rather how much the packaging can contain.

element.name: returnableAssetsContainedQuantity
element.definition: The number of returnable assets contained that are allocated to the full returnable item identified by the GTIN of the returnable asset. An example would be 6 bottles of beer in a six pack (Trade Item).

element.name: returnablePackageDepositAmount
element.definition: The monetary amount for the individual returnable package.

element.name: alternativeReturnableAssetIdentification
element.definition: An additional returnable asset identification type. Allowed code values are specified in GS1 Code List AdditionalReturnableAssetIdentificationTypeCode.

element.name: isPackagingMarkedReturnable
element.definition: Trade item has returnable packaging. This is a yes/no (Boolean) where yes equals package can be returned. Attribute applies to returnable packaging with or without deposit.

element.name: isPackagingMarkedWithIngredients
element.definition: Trade item packaging contains information pertaining to its ingredients. trade item ingredients are required to be shown on the trade item (normally at base trade item level).

element.name: isPriceOnPack
element.definition: Indication of whether there is a retail price physically on or attached to the trade item packaging of the trade item by the manufacturer or information provider.

element.name: offerOnPack
element.definition: Contains details of any on pack product offer (consumer or traded).

element.name: packagingMarkedLabelAccreditationCode
element.definition: A marking, on a label, that the trade item received recognition, endorsement, certification by following guidelines by the label issuing agency. This does not represent regulatory labels like CE, ? .

element.name: tradeItemDateOnPackagingFormatName
element.definition: The format that the date is printed on the package for example YYYY: year, YY: year in century, MM: month number, MMM: month short name, WW: week of year, DD: day of month, D: day of week (Monday=1), ' '-: space and hyphen.

element.name: tradeItemDateOnPackagingTypeCode
element.definition: Indicates the type of date marked on the packaging for example Best Before Date.

element.name: packagingMarkedRecyclableScheme
element.definition: The package of this GTIN is marked to indicate under which scheme it is recyclable. Applies to recyclable packaging with or without deposit. Examples: Aluminum can be marked as recyclable.

element.name: packagingMarkedLanguageCode
element.definition: The language in which text on the packaging is stated.

element.name: cumulativeHumidityInterruptionAcceptableTimeSpan
element.definition: An expression of the maximum allowed cumulative time span of one or more humidity interruptions of a trade item as defined by the manufacturer.

element.name: cumulativeHumidityInterruptionAcceptableTimeSpanInstructions
element.definition: Instructions provided by the product manufacturer regarding the process, procedures, or handling instructions for trade items that has exceeded the cumulative time span of humidity interruptions.

element.name: cumulativeTemperatureInterruptionAcceptableTimeSpan
element.definition: An expression of the maximum allowed cumulative time span of one or more temperature interruptions of a trade item as defined by the manufacturer.

element.name: cumulativeTemperatureInterruptionAcceptableTimeSpanInstructions
element.definition: Instructions provided by the product manufacturer regarding the process, procedures, or handling instructions for trade items that has exceeded the cumulative time span of temperature interruptions.

element.name: dropBelowMinimumTemperatureAcceptableTimeSpan
element.definition: The amount of time that a product can drop below the minimum temperature threshold during storage as defined by the manufacturer without affecting product safety or quality.

element.name: maximumTemperatureAcceptableTimeSpan
element.definition: The amount of time that a product can safely rise above the maximum temperature threshold during storage as defined by the manufacturer without affecting product safety or quality.

element.name: dropBelowMinimumHumidityAcceptableTimeSpan
element.definition: The amount of time that a product can fall below the minimum humidity thresholdas defined by the manufacturer without affecting product safety or quality.

element.name: maximumHumidityAcceptableTimeSpan
element.definition: The amount of time that a product can safely rise above the maximum humidity thresholdas defined by the manufacturer without affecting product safety or quality.

element.name: isTradeItemAVariableUnit
element.definition: Indicates that an article is not a fixed quantity, but that the quantity is variable. Can be weight, length, volume. trade item is used or traded in continuous rather than discrete quantities.

element.name: priceByMeasureTypeCode
element.definition: Indicator to show how a product is sold.

element.name: variableTradeItemTypeCode
element.definition: Indicator to show whether product is loose or pre-packed.

element.name: clampPressure
element.definition: The pressure that should be applied by a clamp to the packaging around the product.

element.name: minimumTradeItemLifespanFromTimeOfArrival
element.definition: The period of days, guaranteed by the manufacturer, before the expiration date of the trade item, based on arrival to a mutually agreed to point in the buyers distribution system. Can be repeatable upon use of GLN.

element.name: minimumTradeItemLifespanFromTimeOfProduction
element.definition: The period of day, guaranteed by the manufacturer, before the expiration date of the product, based on the production.

element.name: openedTradeItemLifespan
element.definition: The number of days the trade item that had been opened can remain on the shelf and must then be removed.

element.name: stackingFactor
element.definition: A factor that determines the maximum stacking for the product. Indicates the number of levels the product may be stacked.

element.name: agreedMinimumBuyingQuantity
element.definition: Minimum buying quantity agreed between trading partners.

element.name: agreedMaximumBuyingQuantity
element.definition: The maximum quantity of the product available to the retailer.

element.name: canTradeItemBeBackOrdered
element.definition: An indicator whether or not a customer’s order will be processed or will remain valid when it cannot be filled due to insufficient stock.

element.name: firstDeliveryDateTime
element.definition: The earliest date at which the supplier can deliver the product to the trading partner.

element.name: isOneTimeBuy
element.definition: An indicator whether or not the item will only be available for order once then discontinued.

element.name: isTradeItemReorderable
element.definition: This element is an indicator that selected styles or trade items may or may not be re-ordered. It does not imply any informa-tion on current availability.

element.name: isTradeItemSizeBasedPricing
element.definition: This is an indicator that an item may be at a different price point than other similar SKUs (GTIN's price within a Style may differ).

element.name: orderQuantityMaximum
element.definition: The maximum quantity of the trade item that can be ordered. A number or a count. This value can represent the total number of units ordered over a set period of time with multiple orders.

element.name: orderQuantityMinimum
element.definition: Represent an agreed to minimum quantity of the trade item that can be ordered. A number or a count. This applies to each individual order. Can be a fixed amount for all customers in a target market.

element.name: orderQuantityMultiple
element.definition: The order quantity multiples in which the trade item may be ordered. If the Order Quantity Minimum is 100, and the Order Quantity Multiple is 20, then the trade item can only be ordered in quantities which are divisible by the Order Quantity Multiple of 20.

element.name: nonfoodingredientName
element.definition: The name of the non-food ingredient for example ammonia.

element.name: hasDisplayReadyPackaging
element.definition: Indicates that the Trade Item has display ready packaging (also referred to as Shelf Ready Packaging or Retail Ready Packaging). Display ready packaging can be exhibited on the floor, a shelf or other location. It may or may not require some modification e.g. to raise a flap. If modifications are necessary, the measurements would be advised for the trade item as prepared for display.

element.name: ingredientStrength
element.definition: Used to define the strength of each ingredient in a trade item or unit volume of non-food trade items.

element.name: isNetContentDeclarationIndicated
element.definition: This field is used to facilitate local business rules where a declaration of a trade item's net content is not on the product label e.g.UK under 50g.legislation.

element.name: statisticalReportingMeasurement
element.definition: The amount of the trade item net of any packaging (e.g. Box, Spool) provided for statistical reporting purposes. In the EU, the Supplementary Unit of the Intrastat Supplementary Declaration, provided when the Net Mass in Kilograms is not acceptable based on the Commodity Classification for Foreign Trade Statistics. For example, ice cream is reported in net mass so no supplementary unit is required. Carpets are reported in square metres, so the area of carpet of the trade item should be shown in statistical Reporting Measurement in square metres.

element.name: pegHoleNumber
element.definition: Used to indicate the peg hole numbers when more than one hole is present in the product or packaging. Peg holes should be numbered from the upper left corner of the front of the package to the bottom right corner.

element.name: pegHoleTypeCode
element.definition: A code depicting the type and shape of the peg hole used for the packaging.

element.name: dimensionTypeCode
element.definition: Depicts certain measurement scenarios (e.g. Retail Display, Out of package) used for measurement.

element.name: nestingDirectionCode
element.definition: Depicts the arrangement of two items that nest together specifically whether they nest against each other or on top of each other.

element.name: nestingTypeCode
element.definition: Depicts whether a nested item fits inside or over the other item in a nesting relationship.

element.name: orientationPreferenceSequence
element.definition: Depicts the preferred sequence of orientation used to communicate the manufacturers relative preferences of orientation.

element.name: orientationTypeCode
element.definition: Depicts via code a display orientation for a trade item.

element.name: campaignEndDateTime
element.definition: The date suggested by the supplier for the campaign to end. It indicates the end of a marketing campaign.

element.name: campaignName
element.definition: Name of the sales or marketing campaign, for which the trade item is intended. Input of user-defined text in order to assign the item to a specific marketing campaign.

element.name: campaignStartDateTime
element.definition: The date suggested by the supplier for the campaign to start. It indicates the beginning of a marketing campaign.

element.name: tradeItemFeatureBenefit
element.definition: The description of features and benefits of the individual product, service, brand or seller.

element.name: tradeItemFeatureCodeReference
element.definition: A code depicting a distinctive functionality offered as a special attraction to the trade item for example BUILT_IN_ALARM_CLOCK.

element.name: tradeItemIncludedAccessories
element.definition: Any included object or device not part of the core product itself but which adds to its functionality or use.

element.name: tradeItemMarketingMessage
element.definition: Marketing message associated to the Trade item.

element.name: gradeCodeReference
element.definition: A code indicating the degree of refinement, features, or capabilities for a trade item for example the quality grade of a ceramic tile.

element.name: materialWeight
element.definition: The measured weight of the material.

element.name: materialThreadCount
element.definition: This element is used to specify the quality of material (fabric) of a trade item.

element.name: seasonalAvailabilityEndDateTime
element.definition: Indicates the end date of the trade item's seasonal availability.

element.name: seasonalAvailabilityStartDateTime
element.definition: Indicates the start date of the trade item's seasonal availability.

element.name: seasonCalendarYear
element.definition: This element indicates the calendar year in which the trade item is seasonally available.

element.name: seasonName
element.definition: Element defines the season applicable to the item.

element.name: seasonParameterCode
element.definition: Indication of the season, in which the trade item is av ailable, i.e. assignment to one of the following collection periods: spring/summer, autumn/ winter or all year around.

element.name: couponFamilyCode
element.definition: A code assigned by the vendor to a single trade item or to families of consumer trade items that can be used by in store scanners in conjunction with a U.P.C. coupon value code for coupon value discount when the proper trade item has been purchased.

element.name: packagingTypeCode
element.definition: The dominant means used to transport, store, handle or display the trade item as defined by the data source. This packaging is not used to describe any manufacturing process. Data recipients can use this data for: o Space Planning o Data Accuracy (Tolerances) o Supply Chain processes o Recycling process (In combination with packaging materials) o Product buying/procurement decisions o Tax calculations/fees/duties calculation

element.name: isPackagingExemptFromRefuseObligation
element.definition: An indication for the packaging of this item that there exists an exemption from refuse (disposal) obligations.

element.name: packagingFunctionCode
element.definition: A code that is used to identify specific functionality for packaging resulting from specific processes or features present in the packaging type. These additional functionalities are not dependant on the packaging type and maybe applied to multiple different types.

element.name: packagingWeight
element.definition: Used to identify the measurement of the packaging weight of the trade item

element.name: usableProductVolume
element.definition: The cubic space occupied by the product excluding the packaging. This is measured as the smallest theoretical space the product will fit into. For example: Liquid - a 12 fluid ounce soda has a product volume of 12 fluid ounces or 21.7 cubic inches within the can. Solids by count- a 50ct bottle of tablets (where 1000 tablets requires 1000 cubic centimetre has a product volume of 50 cubic centimetres or 3.1cubic inches, Solids by weight-a 5kg bag of sugar (with a bulk density of .849 g/cubic centimetres has a product volume of 5.889 cubic centimetres or 359.4 cubic inches.

element.name: descriptiveSize
element.definition: A description of the size of an object.

element.name: sizeCode
element.definition: Code specifying the size of an object and the size coding system being applied, for example L (buyer assigned).

element.name: warrantyDuration
element.definition: The time period that the warranty is valid within.

element.name: warrantyConstraint
element.definition: Determines the relationship between multiple warranty conditions for example “and”, “or” , “greatest”, “least”.

element.name: automaticPowerDownDefaultTimePeriod
element.definition: The default time value that the product will automatically power down for trade item.

element.name: physicalResourceUsageAgencyCodeReference
element.definition: The agency that regulates resource usage for products within a target market. For example Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) in the United States.

element.name: isTradeItemAutomaticPowerDownEnabled
element.definition: An indicator whether a product is enabled with auto power down feature when shipped to the customer. Auto power down is a feature that operates similarly to power management features and requires the unit to enter a standby passive mode after a certain pre-set number of hours of user inactivity.

element.name: physicalResourceUsageSubclassificationCodeReference
element.definition: A sub-classification code value from a product classification scheme provided to drive required information for resource usage.

element.name: doesTradeItemContainPesticide
element.definition: Indicates if the trade item is advertised or labelled as a chemical or contains a chemical that is advertised or labelled to kill, repel or prevent the growth of any living organism.

element.name: doesTradeItemContainPropellant
element.definition: Indicates if a trade item contains a compressed gas or propellant.

element.name: isTradeItemChemicalNotIntendedForHumanConsumption
element.definition: Indicates that the trade item is or contains a Liquid, Gel, Paste, Powder, or Flammable solid not intended for human consumption (ingested).

element.name: renewablePlantBasedPlasticComponentsPercent
element.definition: The percentage of the plastic components only made from rapidly renewable plant-based material by net weight of product (excludes packaging).

element.name: rOHSComplianceFailureMaterial
element.definition: The material used in the trade item that does not comply with the ROHS Directives. ROHS is the “restriction of the use of certain hazardous substances in electrical and electronic equipment". This Directive bans the placing on the EU market of new electrical and electronic equipment containing more than agreed levels of lead, cadmium, mercury, hexavalent chromium, polybrominated biphenyl (PBB) and polybrominated diphenyl ether (PBDE) flame retardants. Use the ROHSComplianceFailureMaterialCode.

element.name: areHazardousComponentsRemovable
element.definition: An indicator if any hazardous components contained within the trade item can easily be separated from the other materials to facilitate product recycling.

element.name: componentsLabeledForDisassemblyRecyclingPercent
element.definition: The percentage of trade item components that clearly label how to facilitate product disassembly and recycling. For example if the product is a VCR and remote control and the remote control is labelled for recycling, but the VCR is not the percentage equals 50.

element.name: doesTradeItemHaveRefuseObligations
element.definition: Indicates if there are special disposal obligations that apply to the trade item for example INTRASTAT.

element.name: isTradeItemDesignedForEasyDisassembly
element.definition: Indicates that the trade item is designed for easy disassembly by recycling facilities using standard industry tools.

element.name: isTradeItemRigidPlasticPackagingContainer
element.definition: Indicates that a product is or is contained in a Rigid Plastic Packaging Container (RPPC) as defined by laws in the target market. A Rigid Plastic Packaging Container is a container that is made entirely of plastic, with a capacity between 8 fluid ounces and 5 gallons or the equivalent solid volume, maintains its shape while holding the product, and is capable of multiple re-closures.

element.name: isTradeItemROHSCompliant
element.definition: Indicates if the product is compliant with the European Union RoHS Directive (the restriction of the use of certain hazardous substances in electrical and electronic equipment), a government regulated agency that sets guidelines for product not to contain certain hazardous substances. The RoHS (restriction of the use of certain hazardous substances) bans the placing on the EU market of new electrical and electronic equipment containing more than agreed levels of lead, cadmium, mercury, hexavalent chromium, polybrominated biphenyl (PBB) and polybrominated diphenyl ether (PBDE) flame retardants.

element.name: isTradeItemUniversalWaste
element.definition: Indicates if a product can be considered universal waste. Universal waste is defined as “wastes that do meet the regulatory definition of hazardous waste, but are managed under special, tailored regulations.

element.name: isTradeItemConsumerUpgradeableOrMaintainable
element.definition: Indicates if a product can be easily upgraded or have parts replaced by the consumer. For example, the ability to add additional memory/storage capacity or access and replace chargeable batteries.

element.name: doesManufacturerHaveTakeBackProgram
element.definition: Indicates if the manufacturer of the trade item offers any take back programs to consumers for the product to be reused, re-manufactured or recycled by the manufacturer.

element.name: physicalResourceUsageClassificationCodeReference
element.definition: A classification code value from a product classification scheme provided to drive required information for resource usage.

element.name: wasteAmount
element.definition: The amount of the components contained in the trade item that are covered by a waste directive for example WEEE.

element.name: wasteDirectiveApplianceType
element.definition: The category of electrical and electronic equipment containing components covered by a waste directive for example WEEE.

element.name: wasteDirectiveName
element.definition: The name of a waste directive for example WEEE.

element.name: wasteDirectiveRegistrationNumber
element.definition: A registration number for a trade item required by a waste directive (e.g. WEEE).

element.name: dangerousSubstanceHeatOfCombustion
element.definition: The amount of heat generated by the item should it catch on fire expressed as amount of energy per pound for example BTU’s (British Thermal Units) per pound.

element.name: dangerousSubstanceName
element.definition: The name of the type of dangerous substance contained in the trade item for example Butane.

element.name: dangerousSubstanceGasDensity
element.definition: The density of gas contained within the trade item. This can be used by the data receiver to determine the total stored amounts of gas within a storage facility in accordance with dangerous substance regulations. Use appropriate measurement for example in Europe (grams per Cubic Centimetre).

For the FDA, Premarket approval (PMA) is the process of scientific and regulatory review to evaluate the safety and effectiveness of Class III medical devices. Class III devices are those that support or sustain human life, are of substantial importance in preventing impairment of human health, or which present a potential, unreasonable risk of illness or injury. Due to the level of risk associated with Class III devices, FDA has determined that general and special controls alone are insufficient to assure the safety and effectiveness of class III devices. Please note that some Class III preamendment devices may require a Class III 510(k).
