element.definition: The temperature(s) that is/are labelled on the trade item to help the consumer understand the temperatures for which the product can be used, e.g. the washing temperature(s) for a detergent.

element.name: designer
element.definition: The person or company that designed the product. This may or may not be the brand name. For example, Guess Jeans designers were Paul and Maurice Marciano.

element.name: namesBeforeKey
element.definition: Part of a structured name of a person who contributed to the creation of the product: name(s) and/or initial(s) preceding a person’s key name(s), e.g. James J

element.name: informationProvider
element.definition: The Global Location Number of the originator of the data. This could either be a data source or a data recipient.

element.name: garmentAdornmentTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the form of an adornment or embellishment to an item.

element.name: ingredientContentPercentageMeasurementPrecisionCode
element.definition: The measurement precision qualifying the ingredient content percentage for example LESS_THAN.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: massEquivalentProtocolDescription
element.definition: The protocol description related to the mass equivalent code.

element.name: additiveStatement
element.definition: Statement on presence or absence of additives or genetic modification contained in the trade item for example "Contains no preservatives, no artificial colours or flavours and no artificial flavours".

element.name: tradeItemLicenseStartDateTime
element.definition: The effective start date of the license to use the title, character or any trademarked assets that are used on the trade item.

element.name: areBatteriesRequired
element.definition: Indicates if batteries are required to operate the trade item.

element.name: importClassificationValue
element.definition: The value for an associated import classification type.

element.name: feedLifestage
element.definition: Identifies the life-stage of the animal for which a trade item has been designed for example Adult.

element.name: aquaticEutrophicationModelCode
element.definition: The model determining the degree of aquatic eutrophication

element.name: alcoholBeverageFilteringMethodTypeCode
element.definition: The method by which an alcohol beverage product has been filtered. Filtering is used to refine or polish the product to achieve a specific taste profile. Example: Charcoal, Chilled.

element.name: totalPackagingEconomicCostAmountBasis
element.definition: The basis amount or quantity used to determine the packaging costs for example 1 kg, 1000 units, 1 year

element.name: lowerExplosiveLimit
element.definition: The low end value expressed as a percent by volume that the mixture is still flammable.

element.name: discountDescription
element.definition: A text field describing the discount.

element.name: cumulativeEnergyDemandProtocolDescription
element.definition: The reference protocol description used to represent the potential to cumulative energy demand.

element.name: isTradeItemADespatchUnit
element.definition: An indicator identifying that the information provider considers the trade item as a despatch (shipping) unit. This may be relationship dependent based on channel of trade or other point to point agreement.

element.name: uDIProductionIdentifierTypeCode
element.definition: The Production Identifiers which are used to control the product as relevant for Unique Device Identification (UDI) rules. Example: Expiry Date, Manufacturing Date, Serial Number, Lot (or batch) Number, etc.

element.name: dosageRecommendation
element.definition: Information pertaining to the dosage of drug or supplement that should be taken/administered per dose. This is not based upon prescribed dosage, but recommended dosage. This may be pre-labelled on product or need to be labelled per target market regulations. Example Take 2 tablets every 4 hours, Take 1 teaspoon daily, etc.

element.name: isPrimaryMaterial
element.definition: Specifies whether the primary or majority material in a composite material used for packaging.

element.name: garmentLengthTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the length of a garment where the hem line falls on mid or lower body.

element.name: dataCarrierTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the type of data carrier physically present on the trade item.

element.name: postProcessTradeItemTreatmentPhysicalCode
element.definition: Produce has gone some physical process whether altered or other physical processes after harvesting.

element.name: usageDuringBreastFeedingCode
element.definition: Indicates if the trade item can be used or not during breast feeding.

element.name: doesTradeItemMeetWholeGrainRichCriteria
element.definition: An indication the trade item meets the whole grain-rich criteria as defined and regulated by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body.

element.name: exceptionMessageTypeCode
element.definition: The type of GS1 exception message being received for example GDSN.

element.name: supplierSpecifiedMinimumConsumerStorageDays
element.definition: Represents the number of days between a product's "sell by date" and its "use by date".

element.name: packagingCompositeMaterialDescription
element.definition: A description ofany composite material used in packaging. A composite material is a combination of different material. types, e.g. Paper-Cardboard / Plastic / Aluminium, or Composite majority Plastics.

element.name: priceComparisonContentTypeCode
element.definition: Code indicating how the value in Price Comparison Measurement is used to calculate the comparative price, which is printed on shelf labels.

element.name: additionalTradeItemClassificationCodeDescription
element.definition: Description of the additional classification bundle (code/agency + description).

element.name: imitationOrSubstituteFor
element.definition: The name of the imitated or substitute product. Example: The GTIN product name is Ketchup type sauce, this value would be Ketchup.

element.name: streetNumber
element.definition: The street number portion of the street address for the contact.

element.name: contactName
element.definition: The name of the company or person associated with the contact type. For example, in case of a contact type of CONSUMER_SUPPORT, this could be the company name as expressed on the trade item packaging or label.

element.name: lastUpdateParty
element.definition: The Global Location Number of the data pool responsible for modifying / updating the party record in the GS1 GR.

element.name: nominalOutsideDiameter
element.definition: The measurement of the nominal (not the exact measurement) outside diameter of the plumbing connection point of the trade item.

element.name: audioVisualMediaProductLabelName
element.definition: The name of the company (called label in the music industry) that made the music publication.

element.name: opacityTypeCode
element.definition: A code to describe the opacity achieved by the product. The codes may vary by product type. Examples Cosmetics, Glass, Paints and Wood Stains.

element.name: regulationTypeCode
element.definition: A code that indicates that a trade item is in compliance with specific applicable government regulations.

element.name: packagingDepth
element.definition: The depth of the packaging, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the packaging dimensions are for a platform or pallet, the measurements for the platform or pallet itself are provided based on the orientation and tolerances for non-consumer trade items.

element.name: consumerProductVariantReasonCode
element.definition: A code describing the impacted change (packaging change, graphics change, minor formulation, etc) for a Consumer Product Variant.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: creditableGrainStandard
element.definition: The standard gram value applicable to the creditable grain gram group code.

element.name: returnablePackageDepositIdentification
element.definition: In some markets the deposit information is specified by a GTIN giving the type of returnable package on which a deposit is charged. Each deposit code is associated with an amount specified elsewhere. The enumeration list is maintained externally.

element.name: physiochemicalCharacteristicReferenceValueBasis
element.definition: Used to express the analytical circumstances in which the reference value was measured (e.g. in 10 g or 200 mg/kg). This is to specify the circumstance of the metric a foundation of the measure values has to be.

element.name: bendAngleCode
element.definition: The type of bend or angle for the product. For example a pipe made to turn a corner might have a bend angle of 90 degrees.

element.name: toxicologicalInformationDescription
element.definition: A general description of any information on any toxic properties as included on the MSDS for example precautionary text on a label. This text should describe the key issues with the product in regards to toxicity.

element.name: numberOfServingsPerPackageMeasurementPrecisionCode
element.definition: The total number of servings contained in the package.

element.name: relationshipEffectiveEndDateTime
element.definition: The day on which the price synchronization relationship ends.

element.name: displayTypeCode
element.definition: A code determining the type of display a trade item is, for example Shelf Display Ready Packaging.

element.name: physicalResourceTypeCode
element.definition: A code depicting the type of physical resource being measured for usage for example electricity, gas.

element.name: sizeCodeListCode
element.definition: Code specifying a size code list. Allowed code values are specified in GS1 Code List SizeCodeListCode.

element.name: totalCreditableIngredientTypeAmount
element.definition: The sum total creditable amount of all the creditable ingredient type(s) applicable for the item as calculated using the requirements, rules and regulations set forth by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body. Per US regulations total creditable amount must be rounded down to the nearest quarter (0.25) ounce equivalent in the US target market.

element.name: drainedWeight
element.definition: The weight of the trade item when drained of its liquid. For example 225 "grm", Jar of pickles in vinegar. Applies to defined bricks of GCI Global trade item Classification - Mainly food trade item. Has to be associated with a valid UoM.

element.name: consumerSalesConditionMaximumAmount
element.definition: The maximum amount of the trade item that can be sold to the consumer at POS (Point Of Sale). This amount may be regulated by law in some markets.

element.name: width
element.definition: The width of the trade item, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the trade item is a unit load, include the shipping platform unless it is excluded according to the platformTypeCode chosen.

element.name: isPackagingMaterialRecoverable
element.definition: Determines whether packaging material is recoverable. Recoverable materials are those which are capable of being reused or returned to use in the form of raw materials

element.name: cancelDateTime
element.definition: Date assigned by data source and stored in the source data pool reflecting the date the catalogue item was cancelled. This date will also be stored in the Registry.

element.name: chemicalIngredientName
element.definition: The common name of the chemical ingredient.

element.name: microbiologicalOrganismMinimumValue
element.definition: The minimum allowable value of the microbiological organism per weight or volume in a specific environment.

element.name: suffixToKey
element.definition: Part of a structured name of a person who contributed to the creation of the product: a suffix following a person’s key name(s), e.g. ‘Jr’ or ‘III’.

element.name: footwearOutsoleTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the type of outsole of the footwear.

element.name: specialDeviceTypeCode
element.definition: The type of special medical device the product is. Example: Orthopaedic, Rigid Gas Permeable (RGP) & Made-to-Order Soft Contact Lenses, Software

element.name: productCharacteristicValueDescription
element.definition: The product characteristic value expressed as a description (text with language.

element.name: packagingRawMaterialContentPercentage
element.definition: <font color="#002c6c">The percentage of the type of raw or recycled material the product packaging material is made from, as specified by the Packaging Raw Material Code.</font>

element.name: exposureMode
element.definition: Description of each of the various automatic or manual exposure (shooting) modes a camera comes with for example, P (programmed auto), S (shutter-priority auto), A (aperture-priority auto), M (manual).

element.name: countrySubdivisionCode
element.definition: The country subdivision in which a processing or other activity has been performed for example processing, bottling, manufacturing.

element.name: organicPercentClaim
element.definition: The percent of actual organic materials per weight of the trade item. This is usually claimed on the product.

element.name: clinicallyRelevantCharacteristicOfMedicalDevice
element.definition: Terms used to describe the clinical characteristics which are relevant for the trade item. These terms will refer to measurement or size appropriate for the trade item, for example 8F Catheter.

element.name: acidificationMeasurementReferenceSubstanceCode
element.definition: The reference substance used to represent the potential to acidify ecosystems.

element.name: quantityOfBatteriesBuiltIn
element.definition: The quantity of batteries built into the trade item during manufacturing. This includes batteries that can or cannot be changed or removed.

element.name: packagingMaterialTypeCode
element.definition: A code that provides the packaging material.

element.name: acidificationMeasurementProtocolDescription
element.definition: The reference protocol description used to represent the potential to acidify ecosystems.

element.name: gpcAttributeTypeDefinition
element.definition: The GS1 provided definition of the Global Product Classification Attribute Code.

element.name: doesTradeItemHaveAutoReaderTracker
element.definition: Indication that the trade item has a device that identifies that the product has a limited number of reuses and is self tracked. Each time the device is used / plugged in it will decrement the count. When the counter reaches zero the trade item should be disposed of.

element.name: yearOfAnnual
element.definition: When the year of an annual is part of a title, this field should be used to carry the year (or, if required, a spread of years such as 2009-2010). Optional and non-repeating.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: codeListVersion
element.definition: The snapshot of the code list at a certain point in time.

element.name: audienceCodeValueCode
element.definition: Identifies the applicable values of the appropriate audienceCodeType. For Audience Code Type 01 (Onix Type) this value should be populated with Onix Audience Code 28 (Books: Onix Audience Code Value Code)

element.name: zoomTypeCode
element.definition: A code depicting the type of zoom the device or lens has for example DIGITAL or OPTICAL.

element.name: packagingRawMaterialCode
element.definition: <font color="#002c6c">The code describing the type of raw or recycled material the product packaging material is made from. </font>

element.name: isBulkUpdate
element.definition: Indicates that the update to the condition is for a full price list update. This update may include price increase, price decrease, unchanged prices or new prices. This price change is managed globally by the retailer

element.name: audienceTypeCodeListCode
element.definition: Identifies the broad audience or readership for which a product is intended. Repeatable if the product is intended for two or more groups.

element.name: seamsCode
element.definition: A code indicating the characteristic of the seams of a product.

element.name: consumerFirstAvailabilityDateTime
element.definition: The first date/time that the buyer is allowed to sell the trade item to consumers. Usually related to a specific geography. ISO 8601 date format CCYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.

element.name: languageCode
element.definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

element.name: accidentalReleaseMeasuresDescription
element.definition: A description of the method of clean-up or pick up for example Chemtrack number in relation to any hazardous materials regulated by ADR (European Agreement concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road).

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: alcoholicBeverageSubregion
element.definition: A legally defined geographical region where the grapes for a wine were grown also know as an appellation.

element.name: propertyFloat
element.definition: A property of a classification of an item expressed as a float for example 0.00.

element.name: errorDescription
element.definition: A message that is returned by the GDSN, if an error occurs during the handling of a command.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: isTradeItemExemptFromSerialisation
element.definition: Indicator that a trade item is exempt from current serialisation requirements, for example US requirements. Serialization and traceability requirements may vary by product and country. In some existing instances, certain products have been granted an exception to these regulatory requirements. This attribute will indicate to supply chain participants (wholesalers and dispensers) clearly if a product is expected to be in compliance with serialisation and traceability requirements in their country.

element.name: packagingOwnerIdentification
element.definition: The GLN of the owner of the packaging.

element.name: productUsageBodyLocationCode
element.definition: Indicates the body location for which the product is intended to be used for example HAND.

element.name: hosierySockRiseCode
element.definition: A code indicating how high hosiery and socks rise on the wearer's leg.

element.name: sourceAnimalCode
element.definition: The source of raw material used to produce the food product for example a goat for milk.

element.name: productTextureCode
element.definition: Specify the texture or thickness of the contained product as a code.

element.name: sparePartsAvailabilityEffectiveDateTypeCode
element.definition: The type of date expressed as a code associated with the period of availability of spare parts usually expressed as an event date for the item for example DATE_OF_PURCHASE_BY_CONSUMER, DATE_OF_MANUFACTURE or DATE_OF_DELIVERY.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: isDutyFeeTaxTypeIncludedInPrice
element.definition: The indicator that specifies whether the type of duty, tax or fee applicable to the trade item, is included in the price. This will vary according to the target market or buyer.

element.name: childNutritionValue
element.definition: Actual value for the child nutrition qualifier as specified in the child nutrition statement or label. For example. if a 4.5 ounce serving provides 1/8 cup red-orange vegetable, the childNutritionValue is 1/8 cup.

element.name: fileDepictedSeason
element.definition: A description of the season shown or depicted within the digital asset. (e.g. Winter, Spring).

element.name: alcoholicBeverageColourCode
element.definition: Indicates the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the colour of the alcoholic beverage. Alcohol colours are sometimes qualified by a a scale or regulation. Examples: Wine Regulations, Beer – EBC, SRM/Lovibond, etc.

element.name: hazardousWasteDescription
element.definition: A description of the classification of hazardous waste managed at the federal or state level for example EPA Hazardous Waste Code of D001 ( Ignitable waste).

element.name: firstReturnableDateTime
element.definition: The first date on or after which non-sold trade items can be returned. This information provides the retailer with any conditions required by the information provider as to the date on or after which non-sold trade items may be returned in order to receive credit from the appropriate party.

element.name: paymentTermsTypeCode
element.definition: The type of payment term expressed as a code, for example DISCOUNT.

element.name: sourceCertificationSystemProtocolDescription
element.definition: Provides the organisation(s) identification that certifies the source. (e.g. Forest Stewardship Council, Sustainable Forestry Initiative, Programme for Endorsement of Forest Certification.)

element.name: tradeItemIntroductionYear
element.definition: The date the GTIN and/or trade item is introduced into the marketplace. Once established this does not change.

element.name: targetConsumerUsageTypeCode
element.definition: A code identifying the type of usage criteria for the target consumer that will use the product for example AGE, HEIGHT.

element.name: variableWeightAllowableDeviationPercentage
element.definition: Indication of the percentage value that the actual weight of the trade item may differ from the average or estimated weight given. For example, Roast beef off the bone 3.5 kg, Gross weight 3500 Grams, Range = 14 %. This means that this item may be produced with weight values ranging from 3.010 kg to 3.990 kg.

element.name: licenseCode
element.definition: A code indicating the insignia of the league/sport/event which a given item bears.

element.name: nutritionalLabelTypeCode
element.definition: Code indicating that the trade item is eligible for certain nutritional labelling programs according to a specific regulation

element.name: globalWarmingPotentialEquivalent
element.definition: The associated mass of CO<sub>2 </sub>equivalents associated with the Functional Unit.

element.name: organicTradeItemCode
element.definition: Used to indicate the organic status of a trade item or of one or more of its components.

element.name: packagingWidth
element.definition: The width of the packaging, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the packaging dimensions are for a platform or pallet, the measurements for the platform or pallet itself are provided based on the orientation and tolerances for non-consumer trade items.

element.name: servingSizeDescription
element.definition: A free text field specifying the serving size for which the nutrient information has been stated for example: per 1/3 cup (42 g).

element.name: exactPH
element.definition: The exact PH amount for a chemical ingredient (not a range).

element.name: targetConsumerAgeGroup
element.definition: A description of a general age group the product is designed for. This would not include the actual age ranges. For example Infant, Toddler, Child, Teen, Adult.

element.name: totalVegetableSubgroupAmount
element.definition: The creditable amount of the vegetable subgroup in the item.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: tablewareTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the type of a tabletop products.

element.name: lastShipDateTime
element.definition: Indicates the latest date that the trade item can be shipped. This is independent of any specific ship-from location.

element.name: isDistributionMethodPrimary
element.definition: Indicates if the delivery method for the trade item is the primary one.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: dutyFeeTaxEffectiveStartDateTime
element.definition: The effective date on which the tax, fee or duty must start being collected.

element.name: extension
element.definition: An extension point for a Price Condition.

element.name: targetedConsumptionBy
element.definition: The type of animal this food is intended to be consumed by.

element.name: apparelDetailSizeCode
element.definition: The size of the detail application/logo.

element.name: referencedTradeItemTypeCode
element.definition: A code depicting the type of trade item that is referenced for a specific purpose for example substitute, replaced by, equivalent trade items.

element.name: communityVisibilityDateTime
element.definition: The date from which the neutral trade item information (i.e. not the private information, not relationship-dependent data and not price data) is available to all members of the target data pool, without restriction. Until this date only the data recipients to whom the data source has explicitly published the data can have access to the data. By setting this date a data source gives permission for wider publication of the generic item data.

element.name: minimumTemperature
element.definition: The minimum temperature that a trade item can be held below defined by the manufacturer without affecting product safety or quality.

element.name: transactionalMeasurementUnitCode
element.definition: A measurement unit code including codes in addition to UN Rec 20 codes used in business transactions including UN Rec 21 codes for pallets, cases, etc.

element.name: isChemicalRegulationCompliant
element.definition: Determines whether or not a chemical is compliant with a specific regulation (driven by chemicalRegulationName).

element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: physicalFormDescription
element.definition: A description of the form of the product for example gas, liquid, powder. Colorless, Fragrant, Liquid in relation to any hazardous materials.

element.name: countryCode
element.definition: Code specifying the country for the address.

element.name: hasDeviceMeasuringFunction
element.definition: Indication if the device has a function which measures any type of patient metrics.

element.name: stackingPatternTypeCode
element.definition: Indicates the pattern the product is stacked on a logistics unit, for example column pattern or interlocking pattern.

element.name: pipeScheduleIdentification
element.definition: The pipe schedule or rating size as defined by an external agency for example Schedule 40 or SDR-9. A pipe schedule is how this is classified in regards to the functions of the pipe including type of medium (e.g. solid, liquid or gas) and pressure rating.

element.name: collectionIdentifier
element.definition: Identifier of the type specified in the collectionIDType field.

element.name: lastUpdateDateTime
element.definition: The date and time when the party record is modified/ updated.

element.name: sDSStandardVersion
element.definition: The version of the standard used to create the MSDS that is pointed to in the SDS URL.

element.name: systemOrProcedurePackMedicalPurposeDescription
element.definition: Descriptive terms to denote the Medical Purpose of the System or Procedure Pack. Applicable for System and Procedure Packs and refers to the indication of the specific medical purpose of the System or Procedure Pack.

element.name: foodBeverageCompositionDatabaseCode
element.definition: A code depicting and agency which manages a food composition database that applies to regulatory nutrition information for example the Government of Canada.

element.name: packagingMaterialCoatingTypeDescription
element.definition: Specifies any coating material that is applied to the packaging material.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: numberOfCyclesPriorToWithdrawal
element.definition: Determines reusability in accordance with EN 13429 or ISO/DIS18603.

element.name: packagingMaterialCompositionQuantity
element.definition: The quantity of the packaging material of the trade item. Can be weight, volume or surface, can vary by country.

element.name: departmentName
element.definition: The name of the department that can be contacted to provide additional information

element.name: garmentLegTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the form or fit of the leg portion of a pair of pants or jeans.

element.name: displayScreenBezelSize
element.definition: The measurement from the edge of physical screen to the frame.

element.name: skinProductFunctionOrTreatmentCode
element.definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify different functions of the skin care or moisturizing product and other treatments.

element.name: targetSurfaceTypeCode
element.definition: The surfaces a product is intended to be used upon. Some manufacturers designate one or more specific surface types from this list to help consumers understand product application.

element.name: handlingInstructionsDescription
element.definition: Information and processes needed to safely handle the trade item. Intended to be sent when handling Instructions Code and agency have not been provided.

element.name: sequenceNumber
element.definition: A number used to indicate the order in which the allowances or charges are to be calculated.

element.name: isReloadReasonCode
element.definition: A code depicting the reason for requesting a reload.

element.name: acceleration
element.definition: The rate of change of velocity. For example: 0 - 60 mph / 4.3 s; 0 - 100 kph / 4.5 s.

element.name: consumerPackageDisclaimer
element.definition: Additional information that should be used in advertising and in displaying.

element.name: avpList

element.name: lastChangeDateTime
element.definition: Indicates the point in time where the last modification on a Trade Item was made.

element.name: upperExplosiveLimit
element.definition: The high end value expressed as a percent by volume that the product will still explode.

element.name: eRGNumber
element.definition: A number used to find the correct section within the Emergency Response Guide. The ERG is a guide to first responders to quickly identify the material involved in an incident for example a fire or spill. It is derivative from the UN Number. Note: The ERG number is only required in the United States.

element.name: packagingMarkedNutritionLabelCode
element.definition: Indication of which nutrition call outs or highlights are on the package. A nutrition call out is a graphic which highlights some elements from the nutrition panel for the consumer to have a quick view for example, Front of Package information.

element.name: editionVersionNumber
element.definition: The number of a numbered revision within an edition number. To be used only where a publisher uses such two-level numbering to indicate revisions which do not constitute a new edition under a new ISBN or other distinctive product identifier. Optional and non-repeating. If this field is used, an <EditionNumber> must also be present.

element.name: financialAccountName
element.definition: Text specifying the name of the financial account.

element.name: priceValue
element.definition: Associates a percent or integer value with a price value.

element.name: physicalResourceUsageRatingScaleCodeReference
element.definition: The value in a range or scale of efficiency of the product is rated, for example, spectrum A – G.

element.name: registrationDateTime
element.definition: The date and time when the party record is initiated / created in the GS1 Global Registry.

element.name: sender

element.name: contactTypeCode
element.definition: Code specifying the function or role of a contact.

element.name: extension
element.definition: Extension point for inclusion of additional information through an extension to the document.

element.name: physicalResourceUsageMeasurementBasis
element.definition: The basis used to determine the resource usage for the trade item for example time period (e.g. hours, days, years).

element.name: partyStartEffectiveDateTime
element.definition: The date and time that the party becomes active.

element.name: minimumValue
element.definition: Specifies the lower limit of the string range.

element.name: proofOfPackagingWeightReductionStandardCode
element.definition: The standard for the proof of packaging weight reduction is based on.

element.name: receiver
element.definition: Identifies the party receiving an electronic message by use of the Global Location Number-- The globally unique EAN.UCC System identification number for physical, functional, or legal entities. The Global Location Number uses the EAN/UCC-13 Data Structure.

element.name: animalNutrientQuantityContained
element.definition: Measurement value indicating the amount of the nutrient contained in the animal food or nutrition product. It is expressed relative to the animal nutrient quantity contained basis measurement. For example, 3 grams in the case of 3 grams per 12 kilogram. Allows for the representation of the same value in different units of measure but not multiple values.

element.name: tradeItemUnitDescriptorCode
element.definition: Describes the hierarchical level of the trade item. The attribute tradeItemUnitDescriptorCode is mandatory. Examples: "CASE", ”PALLET”.

element.name: isHomogenised
element.definition: The indication whether or not the milk used was actively homogenised. The homogenisation of milk is a technical process in the dairy. The milk fat is milled to such an extent that further creaming is prevented.

element.name: additionalTradeItemClassificationSystemCode
element.definition: The Classification System for the Additional Trade Item Classification.

element.name: dangerousGoodsTransportCategoryCode
element.definition: Trade items classified as dangerous goods are divided into transport categories for the purpose of calculating what quantity of dangerous goods is allowed to be transported on the same transport unit under specific exemption rules.

element.name: maximumTemperature
element.definition: The maximum temperature that a trade item can not exceed as defined by the manufacturer without affecting product safety or quality.

element.name: contextIdentification
element.definition: An identification for a context.

element.name: isSubstanceOfVeryHighConcern
element.definition: An indicator that a trade item contains substances of very high concern (SVHC) according to REACH as defined in as defined in Article 57 of Regulation (EC) No 1907/2006. This indication does not mean the contained substance or substances have been added to the REACH Candidate List. Substances of very high concern (SVHC) are defined as: •Substances that are category 1 and 2 carcinogens, mutagens or toxic to the reproductive system (CMR) •Substances that are persistent, bio-accumulative and toxic (PBT) or very persistent and very bio-accumulative (vPvB) •Substances such as endocrine disrupters, which are demonstrated to be of equivalent concern. For these substances, there are specific requirements under the REACH Regulation.

element.name: bracketTierMaximum
element.definition: The upper limits for qualification for a bracket.

element.name: deauthorisationDateTime
element.definition: Last date on which the item will be authorised for sale to a location.

element.name: propertyAmount
element.definition: A property of a classification of an item expressed as an amount (value and currency).

element.name: importClassificationCountrySubdivisionRegionOfOrigin
element.definition: The region of origin of the trade item for import purposes. This is required by Intrastat.

element.name: contactAddress
element.definition: The address associated with the contact type. For example, in case of a contact type of CONSUMER_SUPPORT, this could be the full company address as expressed on the trade item packaging or label.

element.name: contactDescription
element.definition: A description of the contact for the trade item.

element.name: servingSize
element.definition: Measurement value specifying the serving size or portion. In some markets, due to regulation, this information is used as the basis amount that a nutrient is measured against. Example: Per 30 grams. 1/2 cup, etc. Please refer to the target markets implementation guideline on how to populate this attribute.

element.name: tradeItemConditionCode
element.definition: The code depicting the type of preparation that a trade item may require before being sold to the consumer (e.g. cut for sale, portioned/pieced). This preparation should be done by the buyer.

element.name: contextEffectiveEndDateTime
element.definition: The date at which a the registration of a context is no longer effective.

element.name: recommendedConsumerPickupAreaCode
element.definition: The recommended placement for the consumer purchase decision point of the item and location within the retail store . For example a potato salad bulk my need to be portioned to a consumer at a service counter as the purchase amount is dependent on what the consumer would like to purchase.

element.name: awardPrizeDescription
element.definition: A text that describes the awards a film won.

element.name: individualUnitMaximumSize
element.definition: Maximum size of the individual unit inside the lowest level of packaging.

element.name: preliminaryItemStatusCode
element.definition: A code designating whether the trade item has data that the information provider intends to correct or add values to due to pre-production unknowns (PRELIMINARY) or whether the item has attribute values that reflect go to market state (FINAL).

element.name: catalogueItemStateCode
element.definition: The four states are: Registered , Cancelled, In Progress and Discontinued .

element.name: responseStatus
element.definition: The response status for a Party Registration, expressed as a code for example Accepted

element.name: conditionValue
element.definition: Provides a value or percent associated with a condition

element.name: streetAddressThree
element.definition: The third free form line of an address. This third part is printed on paper as the third line below the name. The third free form line complements the first and second free form lines where necessary.

element.name: dailyValueIntakeReference
element.definition: Free text field specifying the daily value intake base for on which the daily value intake per nutrient has been based. Example: “Based on a 2000 calorie diet.”

element.name: height

element.name: referencedTradeItemTypeCode
element.definition: A code depicting the type of trade item that is referenced for a specific purpose for example substitute, replaced by, equivalent trade items.

element.name: certificationAssessmentDateTime

element.name: speciesForFisheryStatisticsPurposesName

element.name: transportationMaximumQuantity
element.definition: The maximum inner volume of receptacles or packages (inner pack of vendor pack) that can be safely transported for a specific transportation type (e.g. Air Cargo) according to a governing agency.

element.name: shippingContainerQuantity
element.definition: The quantity of units contained in a shipping container for example 75 cases (75 CA).

element.name: isNutrientRelevantDataProvided
element.definition: Nutrient Information is populated for those values which are relevant or required to be populated on the product label or label equivalent. All values not populated are not relevant or not required to be populated on the product label by local regulations.

element.name: doesTradeItemContainHumanTissue
element.definition: Determines whether the trade item has, as a component or ingredient, human tissue. The amount of tissue is not limited to a certain amount, any amount will cause a flag of TRUE.

element.name: organicCertificationEffectiveStartDateTime

element.name: registeredStatusCode
element.definition: The current record status of a context registered at the Global Registry for example Added, Deleted, Changed.

element.name: minimumHumidityPercentage
element.definition: The minimum humidity in percentages that the goods should be stored in.

element.name: codeListVersion
element.definition: The version of the applied size code list.

element.name: width
element.definition: The width of the trade item, as measured according to the GS1 Package and Product Measurement Standard. If the trade item is a unit load, include the shipping platform unless it is excluded according to the platformTypeCode chosen.

element.name: isBarCodeOnPackageVariableMeasureBarCode
element.definition: An indicator identifying if the bar code that is printed on the trade item package is a variable measure bar code.
