element.definition: A value for the alternative means to the Global Trade Item Number to identify a trade item.

element.name: isNewDevice
element.definition: Indication that the product is considered a new device in the European Union market. A device shall be considered to be ‘new’ if: (a) there has been no such device continuously available on the EU market during the previous three years for the relevant analyte or other parameter; (b) the procedure involves analytical technology not continuously used in connection with a given analyte or other parameter on the Union market during the previous three years. EU IVDR Annex VI a 2.13

element.name: fileCopyrightDescription
element.definition: A description of any Copyright notice which pertains to the digital asset.

element.name: massEquivalentProtocolCode
element.definition: The protocol code related to the mass equivalent code.

element.name: workingPressureRatingClassCode
element.definition: The state of the medium being pushed through the pipe for example water or steam in relation to determining working pressure.

element.name: attributeValue
element.definition: The value of the attribute that caused the exception.

element.name: aquaticEutrophicationWaterBodyTypeDescription
element.definition: The description of water body that aquatic eutrophication is being measured for.

element.name: audienceRangePrecision2Code
element.definition: Specifies the ‘precision’ of the value in AudienceRange attribute which follows. Optional and non-repeating. This second occurrence of the two elements audienceRangePrecision and audienceRange is required only when a ‘From … to …’ range is specified.

element.name: responseStatus
element.definition: The response status for a Party Registration, expressed as a code for example Accepted

element.name: isReusableSurgicalInstrument
element.definition: Indication the device is a Reusable Surgical Instrument. 'Reusable surgical instrument' means an instrument intended for surgical use in cutting, drilling, sawing, scratching, scraping, clamping, retracting, clipping or similar procedures, without a connection to an active device and which is intended by the Manufacturer to be reused after appropriate procedures such as cleaning, disinfection and sterilisation have been carried out.

element.name: variableWeightRangeMaximum
element.definition: Variable Weight Range Maximum (also called Catchweight Range Maximum) identifies the highest or ceiling weight of a variable weight product.

element.name: laundryHangingAidTypeCode
element.definition: A code describing various accessories/aids used to hang clothing for storage, display, or laundering purposes.

element.name: priceSynchronisationConfirmationStatus
element.definition: Describes the data recipient's action taken on the information contained in a specific segment of the price synchronization message.

element.name: temperatureQualifierCode
element.definition: Code qualifying the type of a temperature requirement for example Storage.

element.name: productCharacteristicValueString
element.definition: The product characteristic value expressed as a string (text value with no language).

element.name: totalPackagingEconomicCostMeasurementDescription
element.definition: A description determining the packaging component, material, etc that is cost and being determined for.

element.name: digitalisationLevelCode
element.definition: A code that indicates the way a record was produced. Three stages are involved in production: recording, editing/mixing and dubbing/transfer. Recording and editing/mixing stages can be analogue or digital. If digital, the stage is coded D. If analogue, the stage is coded A. “ADD” means that the recording was analogue and the editing/mixing was digital.

element.name: dangerousSubstanceHazardSymbolCodeReference
element.definition: A code representation of the dangerous or hazardous symbol contained on a trade item.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: percentageOfAlcoholByVolumeMeasurementPrecisionCode
element.definition: Indicates the precision of the measure for the percentage of alcohol by volume on label e.g. Alc. < 0,5 vol.

element.name: criteriaOperator
element.definition: The allowable list of Operators that may be used in building search criteria for example EQUAL_TO or GREATER_THAN.

element.name: collectionIdentifierTypeCode
element.definition: Identifies the scheme from which an identifier in the collectionIdentifier is taken. This attribute utilizes the Series Identifier Type Code List (Onix List 13)

element.name: conditionType
element.definition: Condition types are general classifications for a given condition. The treatment of the values in a price calculation is determined by the Condition Type.

element.name: doesPackagingHaveWheels
element.definition: Indicates if packaging has wheels to facilitate its transportation. Wheels can be permanently fixed or could be detachable. This could apply to a number of packaging types such as trays, cages, boxes, etc.

element.name: registrationDateTime
element.definition: The date and time when the party record is initiated / created in the GS1 Global Registry.

element.name: productFormulationStatementDescription
element.definition: A textual statement listed on the Product Formulation Statement as specified in the requirements, rules and regulations set forth by the applicable Product Formulation Statement Regulatory Body. The name and position of the company official who has signed the actual statement.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: entityIdentification
element.definition: The unique identifier of the piece of information, such as the object identifier or the document identifier.

element.name: informationProvider
element.definition: The party who owns the data.

element.name: isDeviceDesignedForProfessionalTesting
element.definition: Indication the device is designed to be used for Professional Testing. Professional testing are tests to be conducted by a medical professional and not by a patient themselves.

element.name: dutyFeeTaxBasisPrice
element.definition: The price that is determined a trade item should be set to by legal means within a market. This price is the basis to which the tax is set to. Some trade item prices are dictated by law in some markets.

element.name: flashPointDescriptor
element.definition: A descriptor that informs which action the trade item must be used under to achieve that flash point for example when dispensed.

element.name: pegHorizontal
element.definition: Used to indicate the horizontal distance from the left edge of the trade item to the center of the hole into which the peg is inserted when the trade item is displayed on a pegboard. Example: "2 INH." Required if the trade item is displayed on a peg board.

element.name: componentMultiplePackedQuantity
element.definition: The quantity of containers when this component of the trade item is packed in multiple containers. If all quantity of this component is packed together into one item this attribute is not used. Example: 3 boxes = 1st box has 1 table, 2 more boxes with 2 chairs each, for the table component this is 1, for the chair component this is 2.

element.name: isDangerousSubstanceAMixture
element.definition: An indicator whether or not the dangerous substance is a mixture of several substances.

element.name: targetConsumerMaximumUsage
element.definition: Measurement of the maximum usage criteria for the target consumer that will use the product for example maximum age, height, etc.

element.name: temperatureMeasurementUnitCode
element.definition: Any standardized, reproducible unit that can be used to measure any physical property.

element.name: copyrightOwnerIdentifier
element.definition: An identifier of the owner of the copyright on a trade item. This could be the person who creates a piece of work though it may also be a company that pays a person to create a work.

element.name: xPath
element.definition: The XML xpath of the attribute that has created an exception.

element.name: firmnessOfCheeseCode
element.definition: The code indicating the relative firmness of the cheese based on moisture content. The determination of this is made by the supplier and may be subject to target market regulations or trade organization guidelines.

element.name: isNonGTINLogisticsUnitPackedIrregularly
element.definition: Indicates that the Non-GTIN Logistic Unit is packed in a non-rectilinear pattern such that it is not meaningful to send the number of child trade items in the width/depth/height.

element.name: endAvailabilityDateTime
element.definition: The date from which the trade item is no longer available from the information provider, including seasonal or temporary trade item and services.

element.name: packagingTypeDescription
element.definition: System generated text description of the type of packaging used for the trade item.

element.name: numberOfServingsRangeDescription
element.definition: A text description describing the range of servings/portions contained within a trade item. Some items may contain a variance in the number of units or a range, therefore the servings could also vary for the trade item. This attribute should only be used when there is a range of servings. If servings is an exact amount, this should not be used. An example of its use would be a bag of meatballs may contain 18-20 meatballs. If the serving size is 2 meatballs then the numberOfServingsRange would be 9-10 servings or portions.

element.name: systemOrProcedurePackTypeCode
element.definition: The Medical Device is a System or Procedure Pack as defined by Target Market rules.

element.name: subjectCode
element.definition: A subject class or category code from the scheme specified in the element. Either or both must be present in each occurrence of the composite.

element.name: vintner
element.definition: The person hired by a winery or wine company who is responsible for many of the processes in the preparation, taste and quality of the wine produced. The science of wine making is referred to as oenology. The vintner is the oenologist.

element.name: ingredientDefinition
element.definition: Plain language definitions of ingredients which are consumer friendly.

element.name: regulatedChemicalIdentifierCodeReference
element.definition: An identifier for a regulated chemical for example a CAS number.

element.name: verticalCameraAngleCode
element.definition: The vertical angle used to photograph an object expressed as a code for example PARALLEL.

element.name: isTradeItemAnOrderableUnit
element.definition: An indicator identifying that the information provider considers this trade item to be at a hierarchy level where they will accept orders from customers. This may be different from what the information provider identifies as a despatch unit. This may be a relationship dependent based on channel of trade or other point to point agreement

element.name: dutyFeeTaxLegalProvision
element.definition: The associated legal tax law that the tax information is based on. An example in Brazil: Inciso I, Art. 34, Anexo II, RICMS-SP.

element.name: sizeTermDescription
element.definition: The textual size specified by the size type expressed as a free-form text field for example 10 W or for diamonds G-H.

element.name: softwareCategoryTypeDescription
element.definition: The general category of software by which the item is most closely associated, computers, mobile, GPS, gaming, marine etc..

element.name: onixPartNumber
element.definition: When a title element includes a part designation within a larger whole (e.g. Part I, or Volume 3), this field should be used to carry the number and its ‘caption’ as text.

element.name: isPermitOrLicenseRequiredToSell
element.definition: Indicates if the recipient needs a permit or license to sell the product to consumer.

element.name: connectorFinishDescription
element.definition: The plating used on the electrical mating surfaces of connectors.

element.name: experienceLevel
element.definition: The level of experience or expertise required to use the equipment or device for example: Beginner, Intermediate, Advanced.

element.name: animalNutrientExactPercentage
element.definition: The guaranteed percentage of the specified nutrient contained in the trade item.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: itemMinimumDurability
element.definition: The length of time until which the product will continue to fulfill its initial function and remain safe, i.e. the length of time by which it is best to use the product.

element.name: priceValueType
element.definition: A classification of the price component used to determine how to apply the amount for example value, rate or percent.

element.name: distributionMethodCode
element.definition: The code value that indicates the method of delivery for the trade item.

element.name: doesItemContainAControlledSubstance
element.definition: Indicates whether the item contains substances that are regulated under law as narcotics, stimulants, depressants, hallucinogens, anabolic steroids, and chemicals used in the illicit production of controlled substances.

element.name: consumerProductVariantIdentification
element.definition: The identification for a particular Consumer Product Variant. This identification is based upon guidelines and assignment to the General Specifications.

element.name: feedType
element.definition: Type of pet food or feed given to wild or domestic animals in the course of animal husbandry, e.g. feed material, complete feed, complementary feed.

element.name: vintage
element.definition: The year in which the majority of ingredients are harvested and/or the alcoholic beverage is produced. Determination as to whether the vintage year is the harvest date or production date is according to requirements in the Target Market.

element.name: postHarvestTreatmentChemicalCode
element.definition: Specifies if the fruit or vegetable has been treated or not post harvesting with a chemical or wax.

element.name: partyEndEffectiveDateTime
element.definition: The date and time that the party is no longer active.

element.name: cutForSaleThicknessCode
element.definition: A code describing the cut for items for sale for example THICK. For presentation and shelf planning, the thickness in general terms of the slice are important.

element.name: tradeItemIdentificationMarkingTypeCode
element.definition: A code determining whether the item and/or its packaging is marked with a specific identification.

element.name: consumerProductVariantDiscontinuedDateTime
element.definition: Date on which the consumer product variant of the trade item, which has been manufactured, is no longer being manufactured.

element.name: productInformationLegalDisclaimer
element.definition: A legal disclaimer from the information provider about the data being published in the item message.

element.name: descriptionOnANutrient
element.definition: Any description on a nutrient which can not expressed by using in INFOODS code value.

element.name: speciesForFisheryStatisticsPurposesCode
element.definition: The FAO 3 Alpha code of the species of fish for fish and seafood.

element.name: consumerAssemblyInstructions
element.definition: The instructions on how to assemble the trade item.

element.name: isPackagingLabelledWithDrugFacts
element.definition: Indicates if the item has drug facts labeling. A drug fact panel of the trade item is a label usually contains such items as active ingredients, uses, warnings, purpose, directions, etc.

element.name: vegetableSubgroupCode
element.definition: A qualifier to specify the type of creditable vegetable ingredient subgroup applicable to the item as specified on the Product Formulation Statement and defined by the requirements, rules and regulations set forth by the applicable product formulation statement regulatory body.

element.name: controlledSubstanceName
element.definition: The name of a specific substance the item contains that is regulated under law as narcotics, stimulants, depressants, hallucinogens, anabolic steroids, and chemicals used in the illicit production of controlled substances

element.name: packagingMaterialClassificationCodeReference
element.definition: Identifies the packing material classification used in each packaging component. It is assumed that a packaging material classification would be a broader material grouping that other packaging materials would fit under as classified by a specific agency.

element.name: channelSpecificShortMarketingMessage
element.definition: A short marketing message associated to the Trade item.

element.name: dailyValueIntakePercentMeasurementPrecisionCode
element.definition: Code indicating whether the specified nutrient content for the Daily Value Intake % is exact or approximate or less than etc. One should follow local regulatory guidelines when selecting a precision.

element.name: targetMarketInformationProviderName
element.definition: The name of any local provider of price information for an item if this party is different than the Price Sychronisation Document Information Provider.

element.name: alcoholicBeverageSugarContent
element.definition: Indication of the amount of sugar contained in the beverage for example if sugar remaining equals 6.5 g/l then enter 6.5 GL.

element.name: isTradeItemAPromotionalUnit
element.definition: An indicator used to point out those trade items which are promotions from regular line articles for example a bundle containing one bottle or shampoo and one of conditioner that is released for a three-month period will have to indicate ‘true’ in ‘isTradeItemAPromotionalPackUnit’, while a soda six-pack would leave it blank or indicate ‘no’ as it is a regular trade item.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: storageCompatibilityDescription
element.definition: The types of materials that this product cannot be stored with. Incompatible chemicals give an undesired chemical reaction when mixed. This usually refers to substances that will react to cause an imminent threat to health and safety through an explosion, fire, and/or formation of toxic materials.

element.name: lightBulbBaseType
element.definition: Light bulb sockets, lamp sockets or lamp holders provide electrical connections to the lighting fixture and support it in the lighting fixture. Examples: G4, G5, GU5.3, GU10, G13, Bi PiN T-3/4, Flanged T-3/4, BA75, BA95, BA150, BAY150, BA155, BA220.

element.name: packagingSustainabilityStatement
element.definition: A statement about the trade Item and/or packaging that makes the item sustainable. This may refer to some marketing facing information that is relative to the consumer concerning sustainability for example “Now available in plastic vs. aluminum packaging. Resulting in 15% less energy and 10% waste reduction in manufacturing”.

element.name: regulationRestrictionsAndDescriptors
element.definition: A textual detail needed by trading partners that explains any restrictions and/or descriptors explaining any information helpful about a regulation.

element.name: necklaceTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the style of a necklace.

element.name: lensCoatingTypeDescription
element.definition: A description of the type of coating either protective or other feature the coating brings to the lens. Examples anti-reflective, mirrored, tinted, scratch resistant, multicoated.

element.name: stackingFactorTypeCode
element.definition: Indicates the supply chain process that the particular product may be stacked in. From a supply chain perspective these values can differ from a storage perspective, truck transport, rail, etc. If a retailer is shipping between warehouses or store, they need the information to support their supply chain. For example a truck can only be stack 2 pallets high, but in a warehouse that can be 3 pallets

element.name: tensileStrength
element.definition: The maximum stress it withstands before failing is its ultimate tensile strength. Ultimate tensile strength (UTS), often shortened to tensile strength (TS) or ultimate strength, is the maximum stress that a material can withstand while being stretched or pulled before failing or breaking. Example fishing line test, nylon rope .

element.name: isDiscountingIllegalInTargetMarket
element.definition: An indicator whether or not the product is not legal to discount within a given target market (i.e. the product is subject to government regulation regarding either price floors or pricing practices).

element.name: velocity
element.definition: The rate at which an object changes its position for example 5 metres per second.

element.name: cumulativeEnergyDemandReferenceSubstanceDescription
element.definition: The reference substance description used to represent cumulative energy demand.

element.name: additiveTypeCodeReference
element.definition: A code that specifies an additive type for example an EU E-number.

element.name: warrantyType
element.definition: The type of warranty available for the trade item for example labour, distance, extended service.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: chemicalIngredientConcentrationLowerValue
element.definition: The lower value of a range of a chemical ingredient concentration.

element.name: isOrphanDrug
element.definition: Indicates whether or not the pharmaceutical product is an orphan drug. A pharmaceutical is said to be an orphan when it has been developed to cure rare diseases also called orphan disease.

element.name: plumbingHVACConnectionTypeCode
element.definition: The type of plumbing HVAC connection points available for the trade item for example grooved joint. The connection type(s) will help determine how this trade item can connect to other products.

element.name: servingsPerPackageDescription
element.definition: The total number of servings based upon the serving size contained in the package for example about 24.

element.name: shearStrength
element.definition: The strength of a material or component against the type of yield or structural failure where the material or component fails in shear. A shear load is a force that tends to produce a sliding failure on a material along a plane that is parallel to the direction of the force. When a paper is cut with scissors, the paper fails in shear. An example would be 7.82 KSI.

element.name: isPackagingMarkedWithRegulatoryCompliance
element.definition: Indicator of whether the packaging is marked with a regulatory compliance code.

element.name: consumerFriendlyDateOnPackagingDescription
element.definition: The exact textual type of date on the packaging. Examples: Used By, Freeze By, Exp Date, Best Before, etc.

element.name: recipe
element.definition: A description of how the product is used with other ingredients to yield a new result different than the trade item.

element.name: healthcareItemMinimumUsageAge
element.definition: Note: This attribute is being deprecated in a future release. Use targetConsumerUsageTypeCode with the value AGE and targetConsumerMinimumUsage from TargetConsumerUsage class in MarketingInformationModule. The minimum age to which the healthcare item may be used. For example 6 MON or 18 ANN.

element.name: descriptionOnNutrientQualifier
element.definition: The qualifier from the descriptionOnNutrient applies to a specific nutrient. Sometimes an actual nutrient quantity or % are not given, instead only a qualifier. Example descriptionOnNutrient = * Daily Value Intake does not apply. Then this would only be the * at the nutrient level. Examples include *, @, etc

element.name: doesTradeItemContainElectricalComponents
element.definition: An Indication for regulation purposes of the existence of wires, circuits, circuit boards, or other electrical components in the trade item. The trade item may be powered by many types of energy such as solar, electricity, fossil fuel, batteries and/or generate some form of energy.

element.name: isTradeItemAQualityVintageAlcoholProduct
element.definition: An indicator on an alcoholic beverage trade item whether the supplier has a "declared statement of quality (in French Millésime)”or not. This "declared statement of quality” requires the "Vintage" year of harvest of the grapes to be completed.

element.name: relationshipTradeChannel
element.definition: Used to specify how the trading partners within a price synchronization relation agree to define the distribution or marketing segmentation of products, customers and geographic areas into common groups that are supplied, serviced and measured in similar ways. The Trade Channel may be defined in the context of the Party Receiving Private Data.

element.name: lightBulbLampTypeCode
element.definition: A code describing the type of light bulb whether it is the trade item or is contained in the trade item for example HALOGEN or LED.

element.name: industrySpecificPackagingTypeCodeReference
element.definition: A code describing packaging types specific to an industry for example alcoholic beverages. This attribute is populated using a Local Code List (LCL). Example: Growler a jug type used in the alcohol beer industry.

element.name: discountApplicablePeriod
element.definition: Time period the discount is applicable.

element.name: dangerousGoodsLimitedQuantityIndex
element.definition: The maximum quantity of dangerous goods that may be transported as a "limited quantity". This is the quantity per inner means of containment of each case. For example, 1234.1234 KGM.

element.name: patternCode
element.definition: Indicates the pattern code of the product.

element.name: conditionValueType
element.definition: A classification of the price component used to determine how to apply the amount for example value, rate or percent.

element.name: isBarCodeDerivable
element.definition: A boolean field determining that the data structure on the trade item can be derived from the GTIN.

element.name: clinicalWarningCode
element.definition: Clinical warning information is additional information which outlines special requirements, warning and caution information printed on the package.

element.name: tradeItemUVRating
element.definition: The ultra violet rays protection rating of the product for example 400 or 300. Usually used for eyewear.

element.name: revisionNumber
element.definition: Number to be used for identification and referencing of subsequent updates to a business document.

element.name: isCertificateRequired
element.definition: Determines whether a specific certificate is required by regulation or legal property.

element.name: isSizeTypeVariant
element.definition: Identifies whether a specific size type (sizeTypeCode) is considered a product variant for a trade item.

element.name: naturalHairColourCode
element.definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the natural colour of the hair for which the product is intended.

element.name: organicClaimAgencyName
element.definition: Organization that issued the organic certificate number confirming that the Trade Item has gone through certification.

element.name: propertyMeasurement
element.definition: A property of a classification of an item expressed as a measurement.

element.name: nutritionalScore
element.definition: A score points or ratings, associated with a nutritional program e.g. A - E for Nutri-Score.

element.name: physiochemicalCharacteristicReferenceValuePrecisionCode
element.definition: A code specifying the precision of the reference value of the physiochemical characteristic for example EXACT.

element.name: visualMediaColourCode
element.definition: A code that indicates the colour system used in a film publication.

element.name: usageDuringPregnancyCode
element.definition: Indicates if the trade item can be used or not during pregnancy.

element.name: languageSpecificSubbrandName
element.definition: A second level of brand expressed in a different language than the primary sub-brand name (subBrand).

element.name: subtitledLanguageCode
element.definition: A code that identifies the language used in a trade item's subtitles.

element.name: hazardousWasteAgency
element.definition: The Agency for the Classification of Hazardous Waste. The specific hazardous waste code for the federal or state regulation that applies to the product for example US EPA.

element.name: fileSequenceNumber
element.definition: The order based upon the referencefileTypeCode the files should be used. Examples a 360 degree image, the images need to be ordered, or a safety data sheet where each file is 1 page and should be ordered accordingly.

element.name: sDSSheetEffectiveDateTime
element.definition: Date/time from which the content of the safety data sheet is valid. When issuing the data sheet for the first time, this date indicates the creation date. In case of updates, this date indicates the date of the last revision.

element.name: packagedProductWastagePercent
element.definition: Cost of wasted goods expressed as a percentage of cost of goods sold per annum.

element.name: targetAudience
element.definition: A description of the recommended audience of the music publication.

element.name: packagingLevelTypeCode
element.definition: Provides the packaging level.

element.name: numberOfDividersVertical
element.definition: Specifies the number of vertical internal dividers that separate trade items within a layer in the internal configuration (applies to any level with multiple children: pack/case/pallet).

element.name: dvdRegionCode
element.definition: A code that identifies the region in which the DVD will be sold. Only DVDs and DVD players with matching codes will work unless the DVD player has been “de-zoned”.

element.name: messageCapabilityProxyParty
element.definition: A party that has been granted authority to manage a message capability for the registered party.

element.name: isExtendedWarrantyFreeOfFees
element.definition: Used to inform the recipient if the extended warranty is or is not free of fees.

element.name: animalFeedingDescriptionOnANutrient
element.definition: Any description on a nutrient for animal feeding which cannot be expressed by using INFOODS code value

element.name: colourCodeListDescription
element.definition: A description of the colour code list used to populate the colour code, for example National Retail Federation – Standard Colour & Size Codes.

element.name: additiveStatement
element.definition: Statement on presence or absence of additives or genetic modification contained in the trade item for example "Contains no preservatives, no artificial colours or flavours and no artificial flavours".

element.name: materialStatement
element.definition: Used to indicate the materials that are used in durable products. Material Statement is written as it is on the product or its label.

element.name: materialStatement
element.definition: Used to indicate the materials that are used in durable products. Material Statement is written as it is on the product or its label.

element.name: sDSSheetVersion
element.definition: The safety data sheet version that uniquely identifies the release version of the safety data sheet. This version is needed to make data sheets versionable and revisions comprehensible.

element.name: consumerRecyclingInstructions
element.definition: Expresses in text the consumer recycling instructions which are normally held on the label or accompanying the product. Instructions may refer to the "how" the consumer is supposed to sort the product and packaging materials for recycling.

element.name: isDietTypeMarkedOnPackage
element.definition: Is the diet type specified by dietTypeCode (and sometimes dietTypeSubcode) labelled on the product package?

element.name: titleElementLevel
element.definition: Code indicating the level of a title element: collection level, subcollection level, or product level. Mandatory in each occurrence of the <TitleElement> composite.

element.name: globalWarmingPotentialEquivalentBasisYearsDescription
element.definition: The time perspective description over which global warming potential is considered. Use the characterization factors of the 4<sup>th</sup> assessment report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). A 100 year time perspective is recommended. The time perspective chosen should always be communicated together with the metric.

element.name: displayResolutionCode
element.definition: The code that describes the display resolution of the product. This typically refers to the number of distinct pixels in each dimension that can be displayed, for example 720x480, 1680x1050, etc.

element.name: globalModelDescription
element.definition: The description of the base model. May deviate from the description of Trade Items derived from this model.

element.name: packagingLevel
element.definition: Identifies the hierarchical level of the packaging element, i.e. 1,2,3. For example: a bottle in a cardboard box displayed on a shelf. The level 1 hierarchical level is the bottle (plastic or glass), the 2 level would be the box (cardboard), and the 3 level would be the film around the pallet.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: attributeName
element.definition: The name of the temporary attribute being passed as an attribute value pair.

element.name: packagingMaterialThickness
element.definition: The thickness of a packaging material.

element.name: cheeseMilkAcquisitionTypeCode
element.definition: Allows you to indicate the type of legal mention on the packaging of the acquisition type of the milk for cheese . Example: Farm.

element.name: clinicalSizeDescription
element.definition: The text used to denote the dimensional size which is clinically relevant for the use of the trade item by the clinical user. Use when the clinicalSizeType is coded as "DEVICE_SIZE_TEXT_SPECIFY".

element.name: regulationPictogramOrWarningQuantity
element.definition: The number of pictograms or warnings on a product package according to regulations. Example Mexican and Chilean Food labelling regulation.

element.name: tradeItemMaterialDesignationCode
element.definition: Code indicating the part of the trade item that the material attributes are associated to.

element.name: intendedPublicationMediaTypeDescription
element.definition: The media types with which the digital asset was designed to be utilized, such as Web, Catalogue, Circular among others.

element.name: cheeseRipeningProcessCode
element.definition: The code indicating the ripening process within the body of the cheese. The determination of this is made by the supplier and may be subject to target market regulations or trade organization guidelines.

element.name: powerSupplyTypeCode
element.definition: Indicate the type of power supply the trade item is provided with for example a USB power supply or mains. A power supply is a hardware component that supplies power to an electrical device.

element.name: tradeItemFormCode
element.definition: A code representation of the form of the actual trade item, not the packaging for example OBLONG.

element.name: isCaskStrength
element.definition: Indication the alcohol beverage has not been cut, typically with water, after maturation. The resulting product has the same alcohol content as when it was removed from the maturation cask/barrel.

element.name: layerHeight
element.definition: The height of each layer of child trade items when packed in layers. This attribute may be used when child items are packed in layers, but the child items are not packed on their natural base.

element.name: languageSpecificBrandName
element.definition: The recognisable name used by a brand owner to uniquely identify a line of trade item or services expressed in a different language than the primary brand name (brandName).

element.name: creditableAlternativeProteinPerPortion
element.definition: The portion of alternative protein as provided in the item. In the US this is noted on the Alternate Protein Product (APP) documentation and is measured in ounces.

element.name: skirtTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the primary silhouette or design of a skirt.

element.name: nutritionalValue
element.definition: Indicates the exact value of the score points or ratings, associated with a nutritional program e.g. "-1" or "13" for Nutri-Score.

element.name: packagingRenewableContentDescription
element.definition: The description of renewable content that is being measured for.

element.name: doPackagingMaterialsContainLatex
element.definition: Identifies if any of the trade item’s packaging contains latex.

element.name: isTradeItemUnitOfUse
element.definition: An indicator that signifies that the trade item, that is identified with a GTIN, is a single instance of a numerable device/piece or the smallest package of a non-numerable device/piece. Examples: Pill in a blister pack, a bandage from a box of bandages.

element.name: brandDistributionTradeItemTypeCode
element.definition: Categorization of the trade item to help further delineate product type with distribution type and trade channel. For example: Bulk, Private label, and Custom Label.

element.name: hasCancerousProperties
element.definition: The Toxicity, Cancer indicator evaluates potential cancer-related health outcomes that may occur due to the emissions associated with a given product or process.

element.name: clinicalStorageHandlingTypeCode
element.definition: The type of Clinical Storage Handling of the medical device.

element.name: cheeseMoisturePercentage
element.definition: The amount of moisture content in cheese products.

element.name: searchCriteriaSequenceNumber
element.definition: A sequence number for the search criteria

element.name: totalPackagingEconomicCostAmount
element.definition: The total cost of all materials, energy, equipment and direct labour used during the sourcing of raw, recycled and reused materials and the production, filling, transport and/or disposal of packaging materials, packaging components or units of packaging.

element.name: conditionsToAvoid
element.definition: Conditions, environments, or other chemicals that when mixed with a product can cause an adverse reaction. For example exposing acids to bases.

element.name: discountType
element.definition: A string value that specifies the type of payment discount for example “2 percent in 10 days, net 30”.

element.name: audioVisualMediaDateTypeCode
element.definition: A code specifying the type of date for audio or visual media products for example release date.

element.name: sourceName
element.definition: If the CollectionType code indicates an ‘ascribed collection’ (i.e. a collection which has been identified and described by a supply chain organisation other than the publisher), this element may be used to carry the name of the organisation responsible.

element.name: ingredientCode
element.definition: The code indicating an ingredient (according to regulations of the target market). Select values from the GS1 code list IngredientCode_GDSN, which is based on an extract of the Codex Alimentarius international food standard developed jointly by the Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) of the United Nations and World Health Organization (WHO).

element.name: endMaximumBuyingQuantityDateTime
element.definition: The end date for when the maximum buying quantity is no longer available to the trading partner.

element.name: channelSpecificMarketingMessage
element.definition: A marketing message for the trade item relating to a specific trade channel such as CONVENIENCE.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: labelDescription
element.definition: A literal reproduction of the text featured on a product’s label in the same word-by-word order in which it appears on the front of the product’s packaging.This may not necessarily match the GTIN description as loaded by the supplier into the GTIN description field in GDSN.

element.name: packagingReusabilityStandardCode
element.definition: The reusability standard used to determine packaging reuse rate.

element.name: microbiologicalOrganismReferenceValue
element.definition: Reference values give an indication of which product specific ranges of micro organisms are to be expected and which micro organism contents in the appropriate food products are acceptable due to hygiene rules. Per definition this value reflects a microbiological limit which in a 2–class plan, separates good quality from defective quality or in a 3–class plan, separates good quality from marginally acceptable quality. With regard to the audit of the production processes exceeding the microbiological reference limit means, it indicates there are leak points in the production process and the hygienic situation needs to be increased.

element.name: consumerStorageInstructions
element.definition: Expresses in text the consumer storage instructions of a product which are normally held on the label or accompanying the product. This information may or may not be labeled on the pack. Instructions may refer to a suggested storage temperature, a specific storage requirement.

element.name: packagingRecyclingSchemeCode
element.definition: A code determining the recycling scheme the packaging of this trade item will fall within when recycled. Applies to recyclable packaging with or without deposit.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: itemAuthorisationStatus
element.definition: Code identifying the authorisation status within a specific location. Item Authorisation Statuses are Authorise and Deauthorise.

element.name: deviceSubStatusEndDateTime
element.definition: The date time when the sub-status of the medical device ends for the EU Market.

element.name: specialPermitOrExemptionIdentification
element.definition: An identifier (special permit number) for an exemption or special permit for a Trade Item. An identifier for an exception from a regulation specific to packaging for example DOT T, E, SP numbers, special permits for a packaging style.

element.name: toxicityReferenceSubstanceDescription
element.definition: The reference substance description or unit which is used to represent cancerous toxicity effects.

element.name: equalizerControlFeatures
element.definition: A description of the types of equalizer on an audio musical unit that are available. An equalizer allows the sound in specified frequency bands to be amplified or reduced, in order to adjust the quality and character of the sound. Examples: Bass; Mid; Treble; Parametric.

element.name: cumulativeEnergyDemand
element.definition: CED is a statement of the entire energy demand for a given product or service composed by a renewable part (CED<sub>R</sub>) and a non-renewable part (CED<sub>NR</sub>).

element.name: cheeseTypeCode
element.definition: The code identifying a specific type of cheese.

element.name: audioSoundTypeCode
element.definition: A code that indicates the type of audio sound available on the trade item.

element.name: minimumWeightOfAnimalBeingFed
element.definition: The lowest weight (in a weight range) of the animal to be fed by the trade item. This value qualifies the quantity of feed for the feed lifestage.

element.name: towelTypeCode
element.definition: Code indicating the type of towel based on intended use.

element.name: allergenSpecificationAgency
element.definition: Agency that controls the allergen definition.

element.name: protectiveEquipmentAdditionalDescription
element.definition: Additional information regarding when protective equipment is recommended or required.

element.name: packagingWeightPerConsumerUse
element.definition: The weight of all packaging components used in the packaging system per consumer use.

element.name: consumerWarningTypeCode
element.definition: Indicate if the warning information given in the consumer warning description concerns a specific distinctive feature/ability of the user as age (e.g. Minimum Age 3 years) or weight (e.g. Maximum Weight 20 Kilogram).

element.name: startAvailabilityDateTime
element.definition: The date (CCYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS) from which the trade item becomes available from the supplier, including seasonal or temporary trade item and services.

element.name: productFormulationStatementRegulatoryBodyCode
element.definition: The agency within the target market which is responsible for the requirements, rules and regulations governing the product formulation statement calculations, format and contents.

element.name: packagingCubeUtilisationRatio
element.definition: The overall volumetric measurement of packaging design efficiency. Expressed as the total volume of product in a pallet or other transport unit divided by either the volume of the transport unit or the space allotted to the transport unit, whichever is greater.

element.name: priceComparisonMeasurement
element.definition: The quantity of the product at usage. Applicable for concentrated products and products where the comparison price is calculated based on a measurement other than netContent. This field is dependent on the population of priceComparisonContentType and is required when priceComparisonContentType is used.

element.name: sparePartsAvailabilityPeriod
element.definition: The period of availability of spare parts fpr a trade item associated with the sparePartsAvailabilityEffectiveDateTypeCode for example 24 MON.

element.name: regulationRestrictionCommunityIdentifier
element.definition: An Identifier identifying the community like ISO country, ISO sub division, Municipal zip code for example 10001, 840, US-AR.

element.name: paymentMethodCode
element.definition: The payment method used in the payment terms.

element.name: priceValueCap
element.definition: A quantity or measurement associated with the price value qualifier to limit the calculation of rate to a specified maximum amount. This would be used where a trading partner sets a maximum value for an offer.

element.name: isTradeItemExemptFromDirectPartMarking
element.definition: Indicator signifying the trade item is exempt from direct identification marking according to regulation or regulatory filings within the target market.

element.name: messageCapabilityEffectiveEndDateTime
element.definition: The date at which the registration of a process capability is no longer effective.

element.name: chemicalIngredientConcentration
element.definition: The percentage or amount of a chemical ingredient in relation to the total composition of the product.

element.name: drugPreparations
element.definition: Instructions for the consumer in preparing the drug or supplement before usage. This may be pre-labeled on product or need to be labeled per target market regulations. Examples include Shake before using, Add to 200 millitres of water, etc.

element.name: storageCompatibilityAgency
element.definition: The agency which maintains a list of storage compatibilities for example NFPA.

element.name: logisticsUnitStackingFactor
element.definition: The stacking factor of both the unit load (content) and the platform upon which the goods are carried, if there is one. A stacking factor deter-mines the maximum stacking for the product. Indicates the number of levels the product may be stacked.

element.name: certificateIssuanceDateTime
element.definition: The date and time that a certificate has been issued for a Trade Item.

element.name: proofOfOptimizedPackagingWeightStandardCode
element.definition: The demonstration that the packaging has been minimized by weight or volume in accordance with EN 13428 or ISO/DIS 18602.

element.name: freshWaterEcotoxicityModelDescription
element.definition: The model description used to determine freshwater ecotoxicity.

element.name: audienceRangeQualifierCode
element.definition: Specifies the attribute (age, school grade etc) which is measured by the value in the AudienceRange attribute.

element.name: contributorStatement
element.definition: Text showing how the authorship should be described in an online display, when a standard concatenation of individual contributor elements would not give a satisfactory presentation. Optional and non-repeating. When this field is sent, the receiver should use it to replace all name detail sent in the Contributor Class for display purposes only. It does not replace the biographicalNote attribute.

element.name: beerStyleCode
element.definition: A value to provide a style name for beer products, such as Brown Porter, Imperial Stout, Witbier.

element.name: tradeItemSustainabilityFeatureCode
element.definition: A feature of the trade item that contributes to sustainability initiatives for example that it is made from renewable materials.

element.name: regulatedChemicalTypeCode
element.definition: The type of regulated chemical as defined by the regulatory agency. Example Endocrine Substance, Human Product, Medicine Product.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: isTradeItemAService
element.definition: An indicator that the trade item is a service for example a receipt that can be used for upgrading a pre-paid phone balance, an entrance ticket to an amusement park, sporting event, theatre, service maintenance, installation service, repairs.

element.name: regulatedChemicalDescription
element.definition: A text description of the regulated chemical or formula.

element.name: bracketSequenceNumber
element.definition: The unique sequence number that identifies the order of the price brackets from smallest to largest.

element.name: fireFighterProtectiveEquipmentDescription
element.definition: A description of any equipment recommended to be used by fire fighters for protection for example scuba gear, bunker gear, protective equipment in relation to any hazardous materials for example those regulated by ADR (European Agreement concerning the International Carriage of Dangerous Goods by Road).

element.name: materialContent
element.definition: This element is used to indicate the material composition. This element is used in con-junction with the percentage.

element.name: controlledSubstanceCode
element.definition: A code identifiying the specific substance the item contains that is regulated under law as narcotics, stimulants, depressants, hallucinogens, anabolic steroids, and chemicals used in the illicit production of controlled substances

element.name: isBatteryRechargeable
element.definition: An indicator to show if the battery can be recharged. A rechargeable battery is a type of battery which can be charged, discharged, and recharged many times.

element.name: sizeCodeListVersion
element.definition: The version of the SizeCodeListCode code list.

element.name: plumbingHVACConnectionAgencyCode
element.definition: The agency which controls the standards used to determine the design for a plumbing HVAC connection type and dimensions.

element.name: packagingWeightReduction
element.definition: The reduction of packaging weight with regards to a previous reference state expressed as a percentage reduction or an absolute weight reduction [e.g. g or kg / packaging constituent, component or system].

element.name: fileRecommendedUsageDescription
element.definition:
A textual description of the recommended use of the asset in an easy to understand fashion such that all parties, regardless of specific expertise, can understand use of the asset. This element’s intention is to “translate” complicated characteristics into a simpler textual representation.
Examples: • If the characteristics of the external file are a resolution of 1775 x 1230 pixels, colour space RGB 8 bit by colour, format TIF or JPG compressed to maximum quality. Recommended Usage might be "print maximum quality" and/or "web publishing". • If the characteristics of the external file are mpg, Recommended Usage might be "web publishing". As this value may not be the same for all digital assets, this attribute should be linked to a specific URL.

element.name: city
element.definition: Text specifying the name of the city.

element.name: tradeItemLicenseEndDateTime
element.definition: The effective end date of the license to use the title, character or any trademarked assets that are used on the trade item.

element.name: isTradeItemAConsumerUnit
element.definition: Identifies whether the trade item to be taken possession of ,or to be consumed or used by an end user or both, as determined by the manufacturer. The end user could be, but is not limited to, a consumer as in items sold at retail, or a patient/clinician/technician in a healthcare setting, or an operator for foodservice such as restaurants, airlines, cafeterias, etc.

element.name: sDSStandardCode
element.definition: A code describing the standard used to create the MSDS that is pointed to in the SDS URL.

element.name: awardPrizeName
element.definition: The name of a prize or award which the product has received.

element.name: bracketOperator
element.definition: A function to identify the logical relationship between multiple bracket qualifiers (And/Or).

element.name: avpList

element.name: gln
element.definition: The Global Location Number (GLN) is a structured Identification of a physical location, legal or functional entity within an enterprise. The GLN is the primary party identifier. Each party identified in the trading relationship must have a primary party Identification..;brad_product_recall:PRN.60

element.name: physicalResourceUsage
element.definition: The amount of resources used or generated by a device..

element.name: ringTypeCode
element.definition: A code Indicating the shape, use, or meaning of a ring.

element.name: toxicityMeasurementProtocolCode
element.definition: The protocol code used for the measurement.

element.name: sweaterPulloverTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the design characteristics of a sweater or pullover.

element.name: fileUsageRestriction
element.definition: A description of any restrictions on the ability of the recipient's to use of the asset.

element.name: prescriptionTypeCode
element.definition: Providing a value to this code list indicates the type of prescription that is required. The prescription type may indicate that it is a product that can only be prescribed under the direction of a specialist such as an oncologist, dentist, or other specialist.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: Attribute value pair information.

element.name: organicCertificationEffectiveEndDateTime
element.definition: The date and time upon which the organic certification is no longer effective.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: maximumResolution
element.definition: The maximum resolution of the image device, measured in dots/pixels per some measure.

element.name: precautionaryStatementsCode
element.definition:
Measures listed on a hazardous label to minimize or prevent adverse effects.
For GHS, the precautionary statements have been linked to each GHS hazard statement and type of hazard. Precautionary statements for GHS cover prevention, response in cases of accidental spillage or exposure, storage, and disposal..

element.name: batteryTypeQualifierCode
element.definition: Qualifier to denote the rating and material information are in reference to a battery or cell.

element.name: controlledSubstanceScheduleCodeReference
element.definition: A code that rates a controlled substance based upon the degree of the substance's medicinal value, harmfulness, and potential for abuse or addiction

element.name: physiochemicalCharacteristicValue
element.definition: Measurement value of the physicochemical characteristic.

element.name: languageCode
element.definition: A code representing the language used in the description.

element.name: pantsShortsTypeCode
element.definition: A code indicating the style of a pair of pants or shorts.

element.name: unnamedPersons
element.definition: Positive indication to be given when authorship is unknown or anonymous, or when as a matter of editorial policy only a limited number of contributors are named. Utilizes Unnamed Persons Code List.

element.name: minimumColourTemperature
element.definition: Indicates the minimum colour temperature that is a way to describe the minimum light appearance provided by a light bulb for example 1800 KEL.

element.name: dangerousGoodsRegulationAgency
element.definition: An indication of the agency responsible for a classification system(s) of dangerous goods.

element.name: brandMarketingDescription
element.definition: A marketing description which focuses on the brand of the trade item. For example the history of the brand.

element.name: volatileOrganicCompoundPercentMeasurementPrecision
element.definition: The measurement precision used to determine the percentage of an item that is a volatile organic compound.

element.name: priceDocumentType
element.definition: A code assigned by the Information Provider to indicate to the Party Receiving Private Data, the intended use or purpose of sending the Price Synchronisation Message. The Party Receiving Private Data is able to use this code to determine how to process the information contained within the message. For example, initial load of data, resend of previously sent data or ongoing data synchronisation.

element.name: humidityQualifierCode
element.definition: Code qualifying the type of a humidity for example STORAGE.

element.name: dentalProductFunctionCode
element.definition: Indicates, with reference to the product branding, labelling or packaging, the descriptive term that is used by the product manufacturer to identify the type of dental care characteristics.

element.name: tradeItemVariantValue
element.definition: The variant value for a variant type (e.g. Grape).

element.name: bioengineeredDeclarationClaimCode
element.definition: This code indicates a product that contains detectable genetically modified material for which the modification could not otherwise be obtained through conventional breeding or found in nature. This code may also be used to indicate a product manufactured using ingredients derived through bioengineering that have undergone processes that remove modified genetic material such that it cannot be detected using common testing methods. Excludes incidental additives.

element.name: musicPerformanceType
element.definition: A text description that indicates the conditions in which the recording took place.

element.name: dutyFeeTaxTypeDescription
element.definition: A description of tax type for example "Taxes sure les supports audio".

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.

element.name: individualUnitMinimumSize
element.definition: Minimum size of the individual unit inside the lowest level of packaging.

element.name: tradeItemLicenseOwnerName
element.definition: The name of the owner of the licensed product that is allowing the trading partner to use their licensed name and/or images.

element.name: fileDisclaimerInformation
element.definition: A description expressing any disclaimers which pertain to the digital asset. (e.g. Item may be smaller than appears).

element.name: dosageFormTypeCodeReference
element.definition: The code that provides a description of the physical form of a medication or dietary supplement.

element.name: targetMarketCountryCode
element.definition: The target market code indicates the country level or higher geographical definition in which the price information is applicable.

element.name: dutyFeeTaxEffectiveEndDateTime
element.definition: The effective date on which the tax, fee or duty must end being collected.

element.name: lightBulbTypeDescription
element.definition: A description of the type of light bulb whether it is the trade item or is contained in the trade item for example Incandescent or Halogen.

element.name: cheeseMaturationPeriodDescription
element.definition: A descriptive way to specify a date range as some cheeses are matured over a period of time, but not an exact period. For example 3 to 4 weeks, over 1 year etc. The term maturation is also known in other markets as Aged.

element.name: tastingNotes
element.definition: Written testimony about a products aroma, flavour, texture for example fruity.

element.name: titlesAfterNames
element.definition: Part of a structured name of a person who contributed to the creation of the product: titles following a person’s names, e.g. ‘Duke of Edinburgh’.

element.name: packagedUnpackagedShelfLifeRatio
element.definition: The ratio of a product’s shelf life in packaging to a product’s shelf life without packaging.

element.name: mountTypeDescription
element.definition: Describes the type of mount for the light bulb for example swivel, bracket, tilt, articulating.

element.name: provinceStateCode
element.definition: A code specifying a province or state in abbreviated format for example NJ.

element.name: globalWarmingPotentialEquivalentSubstanceCode

element.name: rankBelowSpecies
element.definition:
Either the Sub-Species, Variety, Sub-Variety, Form, and/or Sub-Form of an organism. All are taxonomic rank below that of species. A Sub-Species is a taxonomic rank subordinate to species. A Variety will have an appearance distinct from other varieties, but will hybridize freely with other varieties of the same species (if brought into contact). Usually varieties will be geographically separate from each other. A Sub-Variety is a subordinate variety, or a division of a variety. A Form usually designates a group with a noticeable but minor deviation. For instance, white-flowered forms of species that usually have coloured flowers can be named a "“f. alba"”. It is recommended to place an Abbreviation at the beginning of the text to clarify to what type the text belongs. The recommended abbreviations are:
  • subspecies (Abbreviation not required for Animals) -– subsp or ssp
  • varietas (variety) -– var
  • subvarietas (subvariety) -– subvar
  • forma (form) -– form or f
  • subforma (subforma) -– subf

element.definition: The code indicating the size of the coffee particles after the coffee beans have been ground as well as the size of whole beans before grinding. The grind size plays a crucial role in determining how quickly water extracts flavours from the coffee during the brewing process.

element.name: roastOfCoffeeCode
element.definition: The code indicating the degree to which coffee beans have been roasted. Roasting is a critical step in the coffee production process that significantly impacts the flavour, aroma, and overall characteristics of the coffee.

element.name: typeOfConsumableCoffeeCode
element.definition: The code indicating the variety of coffee or coffee substitute as prepared for consumption.

element.name: typeOfTeaOrInfusionCode
element.definition: The code indicating the type of tea or infusion, which is generally classified based on how the leaves are processed after being harvested, and the types of tea plants, herbs or fruits that are utilized to make the tea/infusion.

element.name: typeOfAddedCreamerWhitenerCode
element.definition: The code indicating the type of creamer or whitener added to the product, which are often used as additives to enhance the taste of the beverage.

element.name: originCode
element.definition: The code indicating the country, region and sub-region where the product has been produced. The levels of origin required are sometimes regulated, therefore the values represent a variety that allows a recipient to choose which level is needed.

element.name: percentageOfGrowingMethod
element.definition: The percentage of the product or ingredient produced according to the corresponding growing method.

element.name: growingMethodCode
element.definition: The code indicating how the product has been grown, cultivated, reared and/or raised.

element.name: ingredientGroupCode
element.definition: The code indicating an ingredient or group of ingredients.

element.name: ingredientGroupName
element.definition: Descriptive name of an ingredient or group of ingredients.

element.name: ingredientGroupContentPercentage
element.definition: The percentage of an ingredient or group of ingredients contained in the product.

element.name: ingredientGroupQuantity
element.definition: The quantity of an ingredient or group of ingredients contained in the product.

element.name: activeIngredientStatement
element.definition: The list of active substances and their concentration in the drug as it is shown on the product packaging.

element.name: fieldOfApplication
element.definition: The therapeutic indication of a medicinal product, which describes the diseases or disorders for the treatment of which it is authorised or for which there is an indication to use the medicinal product.

element.name: isTradeItemTraditionalHerbalDrug
element.definition: Indication of a medicinal product as a traditional herbal medicinal product as defined by local laws, e.g., EU DIRECTIVE 2004/24/EC for Traditional Herbal Medicinal Products (THMPs). A traditional herbal drug is a herbal medicinal product used with a long history of traditional use in a specific culture or region, often without modern scientific validation (though safety data may exist).

element.name: clinicalSizeValueText
element.definition: The text value to denote the dimensional size which is clinically relevant for the use of the trade item by the clinical user. For example “16 gauge” for a needle, or “200 cubic centimeter” for a syringe.

element.name: drugContraindications
element.definition: Contraindications are a specific situations or conditions in which a particular treatment, medication, or procedure should not be used because it could be harmful to the patient. Or its use is only permitted after strict consideration of the resulting risks.

element.name: regulatoryReferenceNumber
element.definition: A reference number for a record, document or dataset stored within a regulatory information system, repository or registry.

element.name: regulatoryVerificationNumber
element.definition: A verification number for a record, document or dataset stored within a regulatory information system, repository or registry, typically used in combination with the reference number when requesting access to the referenced document or dataset.

element.name: regulatoryReferenceApplicabilityEndDate
element.definition: The final date for which the referenced information remains applicable.

element.name: regulatoryReferenceApplicabilityStartDate
element.definition: The earliest date from which the referenced information becomes applicable.

element.name: regulatoryIdentifierTypeCode
element.definition: The code that specifies the type of regulatory information that is referenced.

element.name: avpList
element.definition: The transmission of non-standard data done in a simple, flexible, and easy to use method.
